1
00:00:25,618 --> 00:00:28,954
SIX SINGLES UNDER ONE ROOF

2
00:00:29,021 --> 00:00:30,022
ON A GROUP DATE FOR DANIEL

3
00:00:30,089 --> 00:00:32,591
Oh, I get it. Is this pickled radish?
Are you making <i>kimbap?</i>

4
00:00:32,658 --> 00:00:34,360
No.

5
00:00:34,426 --> 00:00:36,161
Look, like this.

6
00:00:36,729 --> 00:00:38,764
What is it, though? A tongue?

7
00:00:38,831 --> 00:00:40,266
POTTERY DATE IS TRENDING
AMONG BUSY WORKERS

8
00:00:40,332 --> 00:00:41,500
What do you think about a guy

9
00:00:41,567 --> 00:00:43,469
who breaks a sweat
in a pottery class?

10
00:00:43,536 --> 00:00:44,537
- You seem passionate.
- I do?

11
00:00:44,603 --> 00:00:45,604
Of course.

12
00:00:45,671 --> 00:00:47,740
After I take
the completed utensil rest home

13
00:00:47,806 --> 00:00:50,409
I'll think of you
every time I have breakfast.

14
00:00:52,945 --> 00:00:53,946
Can't I do that?

15
00:00:54,013 --> 00:00:56,649
BUILDING CONNECTIONS
AS THEY SHAPE THEIR POTTERY WORK

16
00:00:57,516 --> 00:00:59,785
Here's what I love about this event.

17
00:00:59,852 --> 00:01:02,021
I don't think
I could've been so frank

18
00:01:02,087 --> 00:01:03,556
while maintaining eye contact.

19
00:01:03,622 --> 00:01:04,990
- Right.
- It'd be so awkward.

20
00:01:05,057 --> 00:01:08,327
But we can chat slowly
while focusing on the shared project.

21
00:01:08,394 --> 00:01:10,963
It's really soothing.

22
00:01:11,530 --> 00:01:13,065
That's so true.

23
00:01:13,599 --> 00:01:15,768
<i>You're here to get to know</i>
<i>many different people.</i>

24
00:01:15,834 --> 00:01:17,236
<i>Right, since that's the case...</i>

25
00:01:17,303 --> 00:01:19,438
- I'll go sit with Ms. Rora.
- Oh, yeah?

26
00:01:19,505 --> 00:01:21,040
- "Ms. Rora"?
- Me?

27
00:01:21,106 --> 00:01:22,708
WHAT'S GOING ON HERE?

28
00:01:24,376 --> 00:01:26,712
- Hey, this is fun.
- Like Princess Elsa.

29
00:01:26,779 --> 00:01:28,247
- This over here...
- So exciting.

30
00:01:28,314 --> 00:01:30,049
- It feels like a game.
- Any reason you made it this way?

31
00:01:30,115 --> 00:01:31,116
WHY DID HE CHOOSE TO SIT WITH HER?

32
00:01:31,183 --> 00:01:32,818
- Hello.
- Hello.

33
00:01:32,885 --> 00:01:34,553
I love collecting magnets like these.

34
00:01:34,620 --> 00:01:35,621
SHARING HOBBIES

35
00:01:35,688 --> 00:01:36,689
I found these so pretty.

36
00:01:36,755 --> 00:01:38,257
- You've been there?
- Yes.

37
00:01:38,324 --> 00:01:39,792
- Isn't it pretty?
- I saw these at Seongsu-dong.

38
00:01:39,858 --> 00:01:43,562
The clover makes me feel hopeful.

39
00:01:43,629 --> 00:01:45,497
- Is it bringing you luck?
- It feels that way.

40
00:01:45,698 --> 00:01:47,032
I actually...

41
00:01:47,099 --> 00:01:48,500
A STRANGE BUT EXCITING EXPERIENCE

42
00:01:48,567 --> 00:01:50,336
- To be honest
- Yes?

43
00:01:50,836 --> 00:01:54,273
the moment I saw you walk in,
I knew I had to talk to you.

44
00:01:54,340 --> 00:01:55,507
- Really?
- Yes.

45
00:01:55,574 --> 00:01:57,242
- So...
- Yes.

46
00:01:57,309 --> 00:01:59,345
Q. WHO DID YOU LIKE BEST?

47
00:01:59,411 --> 00:02:00,412
<i>Me?</i>

48
00:02:00,813 --> 00:02:02,348
Aurora.

49
00:02:02,414 --> 00:02:04,416
- Hello.
- Hello.

50
00:02:04,483 --> 00:02:06,986
<i>She slowly walked up the stairs.</i>

51
00:02:07,052 --> 00:02:08,120
- Hello.
- Hello.

52
00:02:08,187 --> 00:02:11,991
HIS HEART GAVE A LURCH
AT HER APPEARANCE

53
00:02:12,625 --> 00:02:14,827
FROM AURORA'S REVIEW
WRITER CHOI WAS A PERFECT GENTLEMAN

54
00:02:14,893 --> 00:02:16,295
PULLING OUT MY CHAIR
AND HELPING ME WITH MY COAT

55
00:02:16,362 --> 00:02:17,463
- Really?
- Yes.

56
00:02:17,529 --> 00:02:18,998
I WANTED TO MAKE POTTERY WITH HIM

57
00:02:19,064 --> 00:02:20,566
Why didn't she pick my item, then?

58
00:02:22,801 --> 00:02:24,436
Everyone.

59
00:02:24,503 --> 00:02:26,505
We'll now play another game
with little notes.

60
00:02:26,572 --> 00:02:29,308
Inside this pouch are notes
with various questions.

61
00:02:29,375 --> 00:02:32,177
You'll take turns
to pick one and read it out.

62
00:02:32,244 --> 00:02:33,545
- Great.
- All right.

63
00:02:34,179 --> 00:02:35,247
This is so funny.

64
00:02:35,314 --> 00:02:36,715
- It's fun.
- It's so much fun.

65
00:02:36,782 --> 00:02:37,983
Are you having fun?

66
00:02:38,050 --> 00:02:39,318
I'm having more fun here.

67
00:02:39,385 --> 00:02:40,386
HE'S HAPPY TO BE NEXT TO AURORA

68
00:02:40,452 --> 00:02:41,854
- More than at our Gugi-dong home.
- How many...

69
00:02:42,988 --> 00:02:44,857
His cheeks are flushed.

70
00:02:45,124 --> 00:02:47,793
"How many dates a week is ideal?"

71
00:02:48,761 --> 00:02:49,995
- That's a key issue.
- Totally.

72
00:02:50,062 --> 00:02:52,331
- That's so important.
- Is this question subjective?

73
00:02:52,398 --> 00:02:54,099
- It's major.
- There are no options here.

74
00:02:54,166 --> 00:02:55,601
Is that important?

75
00:02:56,602 --> 00:02:59,705
WHAT IS HE TRYING TO SAY?

76
00:02:59,772 --> 00:03:03,776
I don't think a set number matters.

77
00:03:03,842 --> 00:03:05,577
If I feel like seeing my partner,
I'll go see her.

78
00:03:05,644 --> 00:03:07,513
If you don't feel like it,
you won't see her at all?

79
00:03:07,579 --> 00:03:09,381
But I'd miss her every day.

80
00:03:09,448 --> 00:03:13,519
- How many days minimum?
- Wouldn't that be the power of love?

81
00:03:13,585 --> 00:03:14,586
ENTHUSIASTIC APPLAUSE

82
00:03:14,653 --> 00:03:15,654
Minimum?

83
00:03:15,721 --> 00:03:17,589
He's so crafty.

84
00:03:17,656 --> 00:03:18,824
He's as sly as a fox.

85
00:03:18,891 --> 00:03:20,726
At the very least

86
00:03:20,793 --> 00:03:24,196
I'd like to see my partner
at least three to four times.

87
00:03:24,463 --> 00:03:25,798
- In a week?
- Yes.

88
00:03:25,998 --> 00:03:28,434
- That's your example for a week.
- If she has the time.

89
00:03:28,500 --> 00:03:31,103
- I don't think this guy would.
- Me?

90
00:03:31,870 --> 00:03:32,905
What do you think I'll do?

91
00:03:32,971 --> 00:03:34,273
I get the feeling

92
00:03:34,339 --> 00:03:36,642
you'll have far fewer dates
with your partner.

93
00:03:36,709 --> 00:03:38,343
- Why do you think so?
- How come?

94
00:03:38,410 --> 00:03:42,247
He looks somewhat cold.

95
00:03:42,314 --> 00:03:43,749
- A bit like...
- Like I would value my time?

96
00:03:43,816 --> 00:03:47,953
You'll prioritize your own life
over frequent dates.

97
00:03:48,020 --> 00:03:49,655
- Dating life aside...
- Someone who values themself.

98
00:03:50,122 --> 00:03:51,356
- It's the opposite.
- Really?

99
00:03:51,423 --> 00:03:54,259
Yeah, when I have time to spare

100
00:03:54,326 --> 00:03:56,628
I tend to devote all my time
to my partner.

101
00:03:56,695 --> 00:03:58,664
- Only one date a week, then?
- In a week...

102
00:03:58,731 --> 00:04:00,332
I'm up for five dates a week.

103
00:04:01,834 --> 00:04:03,702
- He's such a lover boy.
- He knows what women like.

104
00:04:03,769 --> 00:04:04,870
- I knew he'd say that.
- Same.

105
00:04:04,937 --> 00:04:06,038
HE'S DEVOTED

106
00:04:06,105 --> 00:04:08,273
I wonder what question comes next.

107
00:04:08,340 --> 00:04:10,008
NEXT UP IS KOALA

108
00:04:11,009 --> 00:04:12,010
- Why?
- What is it?

109
00:04:12,077 --> 00:04:14,246
- Maybe it's an awkward one.
- It's too much.

110
00:04:14,313 --> 00:04:15,481
- What is it?
- What does it say?

111
00:04:16,715 --> 00:04:19,151
"What's your flirting trick?"

112
00:04:19,218 --> 00:04:20,319
Flirting trick.

113
00:04:20,385 --> 00:04:23,522
I also need to give a demonstration.

114
00:04:23,589 --> 00:04:26,191
- Try it on Shiro, your partner.
- Really?

115
00:04:26,258 --> 00:04:27,960
It's really awkward, though.

116
00:04:28,227 --> 00:04:29,328
Should I turn away slightly?

117
00:04:29,394 --> 00:04:30,863
SNEAKING A GLANCE

118
00:04:32,397 --> 00:04:33,799
- My gosh.
- What was that?

119
00:04:33,866 --> 00:04:35,100
- Her trick is a wink.
- What did she do?

120
00:04:35,167 --> 00:04:37,703
WHAT WAS THAT?

121
00:04:37,770 --> 00:04:40,339
- What was that?
- What did she do? I missed it.

122
00:04:40,606 --> 00:04:41,740
- What did she do?
- She winked.

123
00:04:41,807 --> 00:04:43,308
Oh, she winked.

124
00:04:43,375 --> 00:04:45,477
Try your best trick on Koala, Shiro.

125
00:04:45,878 --> 00:04:47,746
To Koala?

126
00:04:48,413 --> 00:04:49,782
My flirting move...

127
00:04:51,483 --> 00:04:54,153
WATCHING THEIR HOUSEMATE FLIRT
IS MORE THAN THEY CAN HANDLE

128
00:04:54,620 --> 00:04:55,687
HIGH HOPES

129
00:04:56,622 --> 00:04:57,623
WINK

130
00:04:57,689 --> 00:04:59,158
- What was that?
- What did he do?

131
00:05:00,425 --> 00:05:01,527
FLIRTING WITH A 0.1-SECOND WINK

132
00:05:01,593 --> 00:05:02,761
- What did he do?
- I missed it.

133
00:05:02,828 --> 00:05:04,630
- Did you just wink?
- I winked back.

134
00:05:04,897 --> 00:05:06,198
You winked back?

135
00:05:06,265 --> 00:05:07,766
- How bold.
- Do you actually wink

136
00:05:07,833 --> 00:05:09,168
when you're trying to charm someone?

137
00:05:09,234 --> 00:05:11,203
If someone I like is far away,
I could wink.

138
00:05:11,270 --> 00:05:12,538
What's the problem?

139
00:05:12,604 --> 00:05:14,606
But we're talking
about our own special trick.

140
00:05:14,673 --> 00:05:16,642
Not like an involuntary twitch
because of dry eyes.

141
00:05:16,842 --> 00:05:18,343
- What a go-getter.
- I could lock eyes

142
00:05:18,410 --> 00:05:20,145
- and then wink.
- But tell me.

143
00:05:20,212 --> 00:05:22,247
- Is that your own special trick?
- Yes.

144
00:05:22,314 --> 00:05:23,348
- Are you sure?
- What?

145
00:05:23,749 --> 00:05:24,850
Do you have a problem?

146
00:05:24,917 --> 00:05:26,218
- You shouldn't lie.
- It wasn't a lie.

147
00:05:26,285 --> 00:05:28,120
- We'll let it slide for now.
- There's no way to know.

148
00:05:28,187 --> 00:05:29,788
- My apologies.
- I'm excited.

149
00:05:29,855 --> 00:05:31,290
- What about you, Asia Prince?
- Me?

150
00:05:32,024 --> 00:05:33,358
I wonder what you'll do.

151
00:05:33,425 --> 00:05:34,660
I bet it will be something crazy.

152
00:05:35,294 --> 00:05:36,895
We might get something spectacular.

153
00:05:36,962 --> 00:05:38,797
What if we get thunder and lightning?

154
00:05:41,099 --> 00:05:42,100
My gosh.

155
00:05:43,368 --> 00:05:44,369
My gosh.

156
00:05:44,436 --> 00:05:45,871
- Why?
- What's going on?

157
00:05:46,271 --> 00:05:47,272
My gosh.

158
00:05:47,339 --> 00:05:48,340
- Why?
- What's going on?

159
00:05:48,407 --> 00:05:49,675
I get it.

160
00:05:49,741 --> 00:05:53,946
1-TO-1 EYE CONTACT YOU CAN'T AVOID

161
00:05:54,012 --> 00:05:55,380
WHAT A NIGHTMARE

162
00:05:55,447 --> 00:05:57,282
- I get it. He gazes into your eyes.
- What was that?

163
00:05:57,349 --> 00:05:58,350
How cute.

164
00:05:58,417 --> 00:06:00,118
He gazes into your eyes.

165
00:06:00,185 --> 00:06:02,054
- How cute.
- How cute indeed.

166
00:06:02,120 --> 00:06:04,590
It's a mix of an intent gaze
and a slight smile.

167
00:06:04,656 --> 00:06:07,793
I only smile that way
when I'm with someone I really like.

168
00:06:08,527 --> 00:06:11,496
THAT REALLY WORKS ON PEOPLE?

169
00:06:11,563 --> 00:06:12,965
Show Aurora your trick.

170
00:06:13,031 --> 00:06:14,833
- I can't wait for this.
- Okay.

171
00:06:14,900 --> 00:06:16,168
It goes like this.

172
00:06:16,235 --> 00:06:17,502
We've met, right?

173
00:06:17,569 --> 00:06:19,071
- Yes.
- I know we only met today...

174
00:06:19,137 --> 00:06:22,307
I KNOW WE ONLY MET TODAY...

175
00:06:22,374 --> 00:06:24,543
AND?

176
00:06:25,344 --> 00:06:27,613
ALL EYES ARE ON DANIEL

177
00:06:27,679 --> 00:06:29,615
ALL HEARTS ARE EAGER
TO FIND OUT WHAT'S NEXT

178
00:06:29,681 --> 00:06:31,016
I know we only met today...

179
00:06:33,952 --> 00:06:35,287
but I really like you.

180
00:06:35,354 --> 00:06:38,757
You might've noticed
that I added a two-second pause.

181
00:06:38,824 --> 00:06:42,561
If I hold my breath
for those two seconds

182
00:06:42,628 --> 00:06:46,298
my date will get hooked
and focus on what I say next.

183
00:06:46,365 --> 00:06:50,035
For those two seconds,
our eyes will stay locked.

184
00:06:50,102 --> 00:06:52,437
- You have such a nice voice, so...
- My heart skipped a beat.

185
00:06:52,504 --> 00:06:53,939
- My gosh.
- It really did.

186
00:06:55,240 --> 00:06:56,742
- I got you focused, right?
- Sure.

187
00:06:56,808 --> 00:07:00,078
Not that I do it by design,
but as things go...

188
00:07:00,145 --> 00:07:03,515
If my date's eyes are dreamy,
I might get dazed a bit.

189
00:07:03,982 --> 00:07:05,183
It can happen so naturally.

190
00:07:07,286 --> 00:07:10,555
That only comes with training.

191
00:07:10,622 --> 00:07:12,224
You can't perfect that skill
over a few trials.

192
00:07:12,724 --> 00:07:15,227
THIS GUY MUST'VE BROKEN
COUNTLESS HEARTS

193
00:07:15,294 --> 00:07:16,295
It still makes sense.

194
00:07:16,361 --> 00:07:17,496
What about you, Aurora?

195
00:07:17,562 --> 00:07:18,730
Well...

196
00:07:20,599 --> 00:07:22,467
- You ask to hold hands?
- That's what I do.

197
00:07:22,534 --> 00:07:24,503
CAN YOU HOLD MY HAND?

198
00:07:26,271 --> 00:07:27,272
EXCLAMING

199
00:07:28,006 --> 00:07:29,007
EXCLAMING

200
00:07:29,641 --> 00:07:31,143
That's what I do.

201
00:07:31,209 --> 00:07:32,577
HIS EYES GO WIDE IN SURPRISE

202
00:07:32,644 --> 00:07:36,014
BUT HE EXTENDS HIS HAND
WITHOUT HESITATION

203
00:07:38,250 --> 00:07:39,251
Stand up.

204
00:07:39,318 --> 00:07:41,386
WHEN YOU COME AROUND,
YOU'LL REALIZE THAT TRICK WORKED

205
00:07:41,453 --> 00:07:43,188
I'll ask them to come with me.

206
00:07:43,255 --> 00:07:44,589
She leads them away.

207
00:07:44,656 --> 00:07:46,091
A DARING MOVE FROM A WOMAN IN HER 30S

208
00:07:46,625 --> 00:07:48,360
What did you think?

209
00:07:48,427 --> 00:07:49,761
- What?
- Did you heart lurch?

210
00:07:49,828 --> 00:07:51,330
I was so startled.

211
00:07:51,396 --> 00:07:54,132
She offered me her hand
without warning.

212
00:07:54,967 --> 00:07:56,702
- It's nice.
- Did your heart flutter?

213
00:07:57,235 --> 00:07:59,404
It was a bit awkward.

214
00:08:00,906 --> 00:08:03,608
Aurora turned out to be
an unexpected go-getter of the bunch.

215
00:08:04,343 --> 00:08:06,678
Out of the three women

216
00:08:06,745 --> 00:08:11,049
<i>she was dressed the most demurely</i>
<i>and had such a soft attitude.</i>

217
00:08:11,249 --> 00:08:13,452
But actually,
she was the most proactive.

218
00:08:13,752 --> 00:08:15,654
GRINS

219
00:08:16,088 --> 00:08:18,757
- Aurora is unexpectedly daring.
- Tell me about it.

220
00:08:18,824 --> 00:08:20,659
Her character isn't like her image.

221
00:08:21,093 --> 00:08:22,794
SHE DOESN'T HESITATE IN LOVE

222
00:08:22,861 --> 00:08:25,998
We'll now have some time
for a one-on-one conversation.

223
00:08:26,064 --> 00:08:29,468
Does anyone have a special someone
that they'd love to talk to?

224
00:08:29,801 --> 00:08:30,802
I'll take requests first.

225
00:08:30,869 --> 00:08:33,672
We'll do a random draw,
and you might not get your shot.

226
00:08:33,739 --> 00:08:37,376
IT'S THEIR CHANCE TO HAVE
A 1-ON-1 CHAT WITH THEIR DREAM DATE

227
00:08:38,377 --> 00:08:39,811
TIME PASSES AS THEY HESITATE

228
00:08:39,878 --> 00:08:43,382
SNEAKS A GLANCE

229
00:08:44,016 --> 00:08:45,650
If there are no requests,
we'll move on...

230
00:08:45,717 --> 00:08:47,652
- Wait, I'd like to make a request.
- Good.

231
00:08:47,719 --> 00:08:48,787
I'd like to...

232
00:08:49,354 --> 00:08:51,289
A LONGER CHAT WITH JIGGLYPUFF?

233
00:08:51,723 --> 00:08:53,625
GRACEFUL AURORA
WITH A CHARMINGLY DARING HEART?

234
00:08:54,259 --> 00:08:56,695
KOALA, HIS PARTNER
IN THE POTTERY MAKING SESSION?

235
00:08:56,962 --> 00:08:59,197
I'd like to have a conversation
with the participant

236
00:08:59,264 --> 00:09:01,233
I never got to chat with.

237
00:09:01,299 --> 00:09:03,235
- So...
- I'd like some time with Aurora.

238
00:09:03,301 --> 00:09:04,903
COURAGEOUS KEUN-SUK
WON A ONE-ON-ONE CONVERSATION

239
00:09:04,970 --> 00:09:06,638
I'd like some time with Aurora.

240
00:09:06,705 --> 00:09:08,774
- Aurora and...
- Who?

241
00:09:08,974 --> 00:09:10,709
- AP and Aurora?
- AP.

242
00:09:10,776 --> 00:09:12,511
Why would you bother Aurora?

243
00:09:12,577 --> 00:09:13,745
I never got to talk to her.

244
00:09:13,812 --> 00:09:15,147
- He plucked up his courage.
- All right.

245
00:09:15,213 --> 00:09:16,882
- I did pluck up my courage.
- Sorry.

246
00:09:16,948 --> 00:09:18,450
I was busy with the apple slices.

247
00:09:18,517 --> 00:09:21,319
You can go up to the rooftop and...

248
00:09:22,220 --> 00:09:23,955
To the rooftop?

249
00:09:24,022 --> 00:09:25,590
What did I do so wrong?

250
00:09:25,657 --> 00:09:27,959
ARE WE ABOUT TO SEE A SHOWDOWN
BETWEEN THE RIVALS?

251
00:09:28,026 --> 00:09:30,228
- Please return in ten minutes.
- Okay.

252
00:09:30,295 --> 00:09:31,496
The stairs are that way.

253
00:09:31,563 --> 00:09:33,598
- Is it just us?
- Of course. You get the privacy.

254
00:09:34,266 --> 00:09:35,400
- Ms. Rora.
- Yes.

255
00:09:35,467 --> 00:09:37,135
- Be right back.
- I will.

256
00:09:37,202 --> 00:09:38,570
- Okay?
- Sure.

257
00:09:38,837 --> 00:09:41,239
I'll wait for you
with your fork on a strawberry.

258
00:09:41,306 --> 00:09:42,607
- Okay.
- See you soon.

259
00:09:42,674 --> 00:09:43,742
Sure.

260
00:09:43,975 --> 00:09:45,010
Let's go.

261
00:09:46,144 --> 00:09:48,780
Our ten minutes start now.

262
00:09:48,847 --> 00:09:50,248
A 10-MINUTE TIMER HAS BEEN SET

263
00:09:51,283 --> 00:09:52,384
What a fine day.

264
00:09:52,451 --> 00:09:53,785
THE WEATHER IS PERFECT...

265
00:09:53,852 --> 00:09:54,986
This must be our table.

266
00:09:55,554 --> 00:09:58,023
BUT ZERO DREAMY FILTERS

267
00:09:58,090 --> 00:09:59,257
This is private, all right.

268
00:09:59,991 --> 00:10:01,259
It's a pleasure.

269
00:10:01,326 --> 00:10:03,995
- Likewise.
- I requested this

270
00:10:04,062 --> 00:10:06,965
because we didn't get
a chance to chat.

271
00:10:07,032 --> 00:10:09,401
I know. It's better this way.

272
00:10:09,468 --> 00:10:11,436
It feels like we're on a blind date.

273
00:10:11,503 --> 00:10:13,071
With the unnecessary people gone...

274
00:10:13,138 --> 00:10:14,139
Since we've ditched them

275
00:10:14,206 --> 00:10:17,709
- we can focus on each other more.
- Okay.

276
00:10:19,077 --> 00:10:22,514
I value common experiences or values.

277
00:10:22,581 --> 00:10:25,951
- I see.
- You studied in Japan

278
00:10:26,017 --> 00:10:28,253
and from what I have heard
during the session earlier

279
00:10:28,320 --> 00:10:31,590
you seemed to have
favorable memories of me.

280
00:10:31,656 --> 00:10:32,657
THEY'RE 3 YEARS APART IN AGE

281
00:10:33,959 --> 00:10:35,527
- Well...
- Yes.

282
00:10:35,594 --> 00:10:37,529
I didn't want to lose my shot.

283
00:10:37,596 --> 00:10:39,831
- I mustered up my courage.
- Okay.

284
00:10:40,132 --> 00:10:41,299
I didn't want to lose my shot.

285
00:10:41,366 --> 00:10:43,034
- I mustered up my courage.
- Okay.

286
00:10:43,101 --> 00:10:46,471
I'm very grateful that you did.

287
00:10:48,039 --> 00:10:49,474
I'm surprised as well.

288
00:10:49,541 --> 00:10:52,544
- It's been such an unexpected day.
- Yes.

289
00:10:52,611 --> 00:10:54,679
If we get a chance later

290
00:10:54,746 --> 00:10:58,350
we can chat in Japanese
so our Japanese won't get rusty.

291
00:10:58,416 --> 00:11:00,752
- I'd love that.
- Like our own little study group.

292
00:11:00,819 --> 00:11:04,122
I believe that'd be a nice way
to spend time together.

293
00:11:04,189 --> 00:11:05,857
I'd like to spend more time with you

294
00:11:06,258 --> 00:11:08,193
- I look forward to it.
- in the future.

295
00:11:10,228 --> 00:11:14,065
WHAT DO THE PHRASES "LATER"
AND "IN THE FUTURE" IMPLY?

296
00:11:14,132 --> 00:11:15,300
If we get the chance, of course.

297
00:11:17,702 --> 00:11:19,804
There's this word I like very much.

298
00:11:20,038 --> 00:11:21,139
- What is it?
- Well...

299
00:11:21,573 --> 00:11:24,743
I like enduring connections.

300
00:11:25,310 --> 00:11:26,945
May I ask why?

301
00:11:27,879 --> 00:11:28,880
Personally

302
00:11:29,481 --> 00:11:34,753
I tend to cherish the connections
we form in our lives.

303
00:11:34,819 --> 00:11:36,821
Even if it's a brief encounter.

304
00:11:37,422 --> 00:11:41,826
I believe people come
into our lives for a reason.

305
00:11:42,827 --> 00:11:45,330
Our encounter today

306
00:11:45,397 --> 00:11:48,233
may be the start
of a beautiful relationship.

307
00:11:48,300 --> 00:11:49,401
MAYBE IT'S FATE

308
00:11:49,467 --> 00:11:52,237
I'll remember this day fondly.

309
00:11:52,304 --> 00:11:55,607
I also feel the same way.

310
00:11:58,076 --> 00:11:59,477
Hopefully, we can meet again.

311
00:12:02,380 --> 00:12:04,216
I hope we can laugh
over funny stories in Japanese

312
00:12:04,282 --> 00:12:07,586
- or enjoy a nice meal together.
- I'd love that.

313
00:12:08,820 --> 00:12:10,121
Let's make a pinky promise.

314
00:12:10,188 --> 00:12:11,856
Let's make a pinky promise.

315
00:12:15,360 --> 00:12:17,028
Isn't this flirting?

316
00:12:17,095 --> 00:12:18,096
Gosh.

317
00:12:19,598 --> 00:12:20,799
How long do we have left?

318
00:12:21,866 --> 00:12:24,803
I hope our connection today
will blossom into a beautiful one.

319
00:12:24,869 --> 00:12:26,471
- Me too.
- Great.

320
00:12:26,538 --> 00:12:28,173
AP AND AURORA'S
ONE-ON-ONE CONVERSATION ENDS

321
00:12:28,240 --> 00:12:29,441
Thank you.

322
00:12:29,874 --> 00:12:31,309
Nice to meet you, Ms. Ala.

323
00:12:31,376 --> 00:12:33,111
- "Nice to meet you, Ms. Ala"?
- Yes, Ms. Ala.

324
00:12:33,178 --> 00:12:34,246
- Ms. Ala?
- Ms. Ala.

325
00:12:34,579 --> 00:12:37,015
- We only have five minutes.
- Yes.

326
00:12:37,082 --> 00:12:40,051
How about we speak casually?
Would it be okay with you?

327
00:12:40,252 --> 00:12:41,353
Go ahead.

328
00:12:41,419 --> 00:12:42,621
You're older than me.

329
00:12:42,687 --> 00:12:43,688
Okay, thanks.

330
00:12:43,755 --> 00:12:44,789
I'M JUST JOKING

331
00:12:44,856 --> 00:12:48,793
I got the sense that you enjoy
cheerful and funny things.

332
00:12:49,861 --> 00:12:51,429
- I'm an inquisitive type.
- You are?

333
00:12:51,496 --> 00:12:52,864
Yes, you can say that I am.

334
00:12:52,931 --> 00:12:54,866
I also have lots of interests.

335
00:12:55,066 --> 00:12:57,335
- I want to lead a cheerful life.
- Really?

336
00:12:57,402 --> 00:12:59,404
But I think you also have a serious

337
00:12:59,471 --> 00:13:00,939
- old-fashioned side.
- That's true.

338
00:13:01,006 --> 00:13:03,575
How did you know?
Are you a fortune teller?

339
00:13:03,908 --> 00:13:06,511
- How did you see right through me?
- That's the vibe I'm getting.

340
00:13:06,578 --> 00:13:08,313
Are you similar in that regard?

341
00:13:08,380 --> 00:13:09,614
- Me?
- Yes.

342
00:13:10,081 --> 00:13:11,349
I'm rather...

343
00:13:11,416 --> 00:13:15,253
I'm the type who gives up things
for the peace of mind.

344
00:13:15,320 --> 00:13:16,721
That's the kind of guy I am.

345
00:13:17,289 --> 00:13:18,323
Well...

346
00:13:18,390 --> 00:13:20,125
If I try to keep someone or something

347
00:13:20,191 --> 00:13:21,726
it'll be a struggle to hold on.

348
00:13:21,793 --> 00:13:23,662
But if I let go, I'll be a free man.

349
00:13:23,728 --> 00:13:25,530
That's the kind of person I am.

350
00:13:25,597 --> 00:13:27,499
That's how relationships fall apart.

351
00:13:27,565 --> 00:13:29,301
BRUTAL HONESTY

352
00:13:29,601 --> 00:13:32,103
- That's true.
- It will lead to ruin.

353
00:13:32,937 --> 00:13:35,307
Any woman will think
that you're not interested

354
00:13:35,373 --> 00:13:37,709
or that you don't care enough.

355
00:13:39,010 --> 00:13:40,278
- She'll end it.
- That's true.

356
00:13:40,345 --> 00:13:42,547
That's probably why...

357
00:13:43,581 --> 00:13:46,351
it takes time for me
to win someone over

358
00:13:46,418 --> 00:13:48,720
or to find someone at all.

359
00:13:48,787 --> 00:13:50,522
I don't know. That's how I see it.

360
00:13:50,588 --> 00:13:51,856
Back in the day

361
00:13:51,923 --> 00:13:54,359
I used to fall in love so easily

362
00:13:54,426 --> 00:13:56,494
and act rather possessively
until I realized

363
00:13:56,561 --> 00:13:58,697
that the more I tried
to make my partner solely mine

364
00:13:58,763 --> 00:14:00,131
the more we grew apart.

365
00:14:00,198 --> 00:14:02,500
I've come to think
that if I leave my partner be

366
00:14:02,567 --> 00:14:06,438
she'll stay with me when she wants to
and move on at her own pace.

367
00:14:06,504 --> 00:14:08,039
Can she just drop by and leave?

368
00:14:08,106 --> 00:14:11,943
I've changed my ways
because keeping her by my side

369
00:14:12,010 --> 00:14:13,378
led to a falling out.

370
00:14:13,445 --> 00:14:15,413
That's how things are with me.

371
00:14:15,480 --> 00:14:16,915
I don't even know what I'm saying.

372
00:14:16,981 --> 00:14:18,249
I think I get the idea.

373
00:14:18,316 --> 00:14:19,684
- You do?
- Yes.

374
00:14:20,251 --> 00:14:21,720
You sound like a sage.

375
00:14:22,387 --> 00:14:25,657
A sage would say,
"I have a suggestion for you."

376
00:14:25,724 --> 00:14:26,858
THE END SIGNAL

377
00:14:26,925 --> 00:14:28,293
What's this?

378
00:14:28,360 --> 00:14:29,461
How do I stop this?

379
00:14:29,527 --> 00:14:30,528
SOMEWHAT SAD TO SEE IT END

380
00:14:30,962 --> 00:14:32,530
Our time together came to an end.

381
00:14:32,597 --> 00:14:34,966
Let's chat a bit more.
I don't think they caught on.

382
00:14:35,500 --> 00:14:37,335
LET'S CHECK ON SHIRO AND JIGGLYPUFF

383
00:14:37,569 --> 00:14:42,674
What type of person
did you want to talk to

384
00:14:42,741 --> 00:14:44,442
in terms of personality?

385
00:14:44,976 --> 00:14:47,579
I wanted to talk to you, Jigglypuff.

386
00:14:48,847 --> 00:14:50,882
Why did you want to talk to me?

387
00:14:53,451 --> 00:14:55,387
We made eye contact most often

388
00:14:55,820 --> 00:14:57,922
so I wanted to get to know you.

389
00:14:59,724 --> 00:15:02,794
Did you choose the dental floss
because the container was cute?

390
00:15:02,861 --> 00:15:03,995
Yes.

391
00:15:04,062 --> 00:15:05,897
Actually, well...

392
00:15:05,964 --> 00:15:07,699
This is a secret.

393
00:15:09,501 --> 00:15:14,906
- I saw you using floss on the show.
- Yes, that's right.

394
00:15:14,973 --> 00:15:17,208
I assumed it was yours.

395
00:15:18,143 --> 00:15:19,210
I assumed it was yours.

396
00:15:19,277 --> 00:15:20,545
ACTUALLY, SHE WAS INTERESTED IN SHIRO

397
00:15:20,612 --> 00:15:22,080
You wanted to talk to me.

398
00:15:22,514 --> 00:15:23,515
SAD TO HAVE MISSED THE CHANCE

399
00:15:24,015 --> 00:15:25,583
- Are you okay?
- I'm good.

400
00:15:25,650 --> 00:15:27,519
I just dropped onto the seat.

401
00:15:28,720 --> 00:15:30,355
<i>It's time for the final choice.</i>

402
00:15:30,422 --> 00:15:33,057
<i>Remember the number</i>
<i>I sent you in the initial message?</i>

403
00:15:33,124 --> 00:15:36,394
<i>Text me the nickname of the person</i>
<i>you're interested in.</i>

404
00:15:37,228 --> 00:15:40,799
EVEN THE AIR FELT DIFFERENT
DURING THE FIRST-EVER GROUP DATE

405
00:15:40,999 --> 00:15:42,734
We're so cheerful today, aren't we?

406
00:15:42,801 --> 00:15:44,235
We've never been this way at home.

407
00:15:45,136 --> 00:15:46,137
Oh, that's how it is?

408
00:15:47,138 --> 00:15:49,874
You have beautiful hands
with long fingers.

409
00:15:49,941 --> 00:15:52,043
After I take
the completed utensil rest home

410
00:15:52,110 --> 00:15:54,546
I'll think of you
every time I have breakfast.

411
00:15:54,612 --> 00:15:55,914
THEY CRAFTED NEW MEMORIES TOGETHER

412
00:15:56,181 --> 00:15:58,383
Were you excited?

413
00:15:58,450 --> 00:15:59,684
Yes, I was.

414
00:15:59,751 --> 00:16:01,953
I'm having fun,
and I'm far more relaxed now

415
00:16:02,020 --> 00:16:03,388
compared to earlier.

416
00:16:03,455 --> 00:16:06,624
I'll let you know the results
via text before midnight.

417
00:16:06,691 --> 00:16:07,692
POTTERY DATE'S RULE

418
00:16:07,759 --> 00:16:10,094
IF YOU GET MATCHED,
YOU'LL RECEIVE THEIR NUMBER

419
00:16:10,161 --> 00:16:11,196
Please send me the text now.

420
00:16:11,262 --> 00:16:14,232
DO PEOPLE NOT ASK FOR NUMBERS
THEMSELVES THESE DAYS?

421
00:16:16,501 --> 00:16:18,703
I didn't get to chat with Ms. Rora.

422
00:16:18,770 --> 00:16:20,038
Yes, it's such a bummer.

423
00:16:20,104 --> 00:16:21,406
- I wanted to talk some more.
- Me too.

424
00:16:21,473 --> 00:16:23,174
But AP had to snatch you away.

425
00:16:25,143 --> 00:16:28,379
Did you have fun with AP?
Was it kind of serious?

426
00:16:28,446 --> 00:16:29,781
It was on the serious side.

427
00:16:31,516 --> 00:16:32,817
I see.

428
00:16:32,884 --> 00:16:34,385
Was it deep and serious?

429
00:16:38,089 --> 00:16:39,090
Okay.

430
00:16:39,157 --> 00:16:42,527
NO ONE KNOWS
WHERE THEIR HEARTS ARE HEADED

431
00:16:43,962 --> 00:16:45,196
EVERYONE SHARED THEIR MIND

432
00:16:45,263 --> 00:16:47,065
You're writing such a long text.

433
00:16:47,699 --> 00:16:49,367
That's a wrap on today's group date.

434
00:16:49,434 --> 00:16:50,468
Your pottery will be ready

435
00:16:50,535 --> 00:16:51,703
- in three weeks.
- Okay.

436
00:16:51,903 --> 00:16:53,505
- Please look forward to them.
- Okay.

437
00:16:53,571 --> 00:16:55,440
I hope we'll see many matches today.

438
00:16:55,507 --> 00:16:57,275
- Thank you for everything.
- Thank you.

439
00:16:57,342 --> 00:16:58,743
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

440
00:16:58,810 --> 00:17:00,011
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

441
00:17:00,078 --> 00:17:01,312
It was so nice meeting you.

442
00:17:01,679 --> 00:17:03,181
- Did you have fun?
- I sure did.

443
00:17:03,248 --> 00:17:04,616
I enjoyed it, too.

444
00:17:04,682 --> 00:17:07,252
- This was a new experience for me.
- Same.

445
00:17:07,318 --> 00:17:09,387
It kind of brings you back
to the good old days, right?

446
00:17:11,322 --> 00:17:12,323
It was a great pleasure.

447
00:17:12,390 --> 00:17:13,458
Likewise.

448
00:17:13,525 --> 00:17:16,060
Has our compatibility increased?

449
00:17:16,127 --> 00:17:19,264
It reached 60 to 70 percent for me.

450
00:17:19,330 --> 00:17:20,665
- It reached 60 to 70 percent?
- Yes.

451
00:17:20,932 --> 00:17:22,100
Same.

452
00:17:22,166 --> 00:17:23,368
- Really?
- Yes.

453
00:17:23,434 --> 00:17:25,470
He's putting forth his last spurt.

454
00:17:27,839 --> 00:17:29,507
Can I help you with your coat?
It's cold outside.

455
00:17:29,574 --> 00:17:30,575
Enjoy your dinner.

456
00:17:30,642 --> 00:17:32,310
- Get home safely.
- I'll get going. Bye.

457
00:17:32,377 --> 00:17:34,479
- You'll need to put it on anyway.
- Oh, gosh.

458
00:17:34,913 --> 00:17:35,980
Thank you.

459
00:17:36,314 --> 00:17:37,715
- Hold out your arms low.
- Okay.

460
00:17:37,782 --> 00:17:39,517
CLINGING TO HER UNTIL THE LAST MINUTE

461
00:17:40,485 --> 00:17:41,586
He must be interested.

462
00:17:42,253 --> 00:17:43,454
I think he's really into her.

463
00:17:43,521 --> 00:17:44,789
- I enjoyed today.
- Of course.

464
00:17:44,856 --> 00:17:45,857
- Bye.
- Take care.

465
00:17:45,924 --> 00:17:47,158
Thank you.

466
00:17:47,225 --> 00:17:48,893
SEEING AURORA OFF

467
00:17:52,330 --> 00:17:54,332
- Feels like my body's melting.
- Oh, man.

468
00:17:54,399 --> 00:17:56,701
Why is my heart flip-flopping?

469
00:17:58,570 --> 00:18:03,875
BASKING IN THE LINGERING EXCITEMENT
THEY HAD GONE WITHOUT FOR SO LONG

470
00:18:04,642 --> 00:18:05,944
Let's get going.

471
00:18:06,010 --> 00:18:09,380
- Let's head home.
- I feel kind of dumbstruck now.

472
00:18:09,747 --> 00:18:11,683
<i>It was nice to feel young again.</i>

473
00:18:11,749 --> 00:18:13,084
<i>Yes, it was...</i>

474
00:18:13,151 --> 00:18:14,485
DANIEL'S HOUSE SQUAD GOAL
GROUP DATE AT FORTY

475
00:18:14,552 --> 00:18:17,121
<i>- My heart lurched.</i>
<i>- It was a new experience.</i>

476
00:18:17,188 --> 00:18:18,957
We had so much fun thanks to you.

477
00:18:19,023 --> 00:18:20,124
- Really?
- Yes.

478
00:18:20,825 --> 00:18:21,826
You guys did seem excited.

479
00:18:21,893 --> 00:18:23,394
When else could we try
something like this?

480
00:18:23,461 --> 00:18:26,297
I got to relive the rush of emotions
I felt as a 20-year-old.

481
00:18:26,364 --> 00:18:27,632
And, well...

482
00:18:27,699 --> 00:18:30,635
It's been a while
since I felt so giddy.

483
00:18:30,702 --> 00:18:32,770
It was a strange sensation

484
00:18:32,837 --> 00:18:35,506
- like your hair was standing on end.
- Exactly.

485
00:18:35,573 --> 00:18:37,742
Back in the Gugi-dong house

486
00:18:38,810 --> 00:18:41,512
<i>- we heard loud guffaws.</i>
<i>- Definitely.</i>

487
00:18:41,579 --> 00:18:43,514
<i>But over here,</i>
<i>the ladies had tinkling laughter.</i>

488
00:18:44,415 --> 00:18:45,783
It was definitely new.

489
00:18:45,850 --> 00:18:48,686
A DAY THAT FELT LIKE A BIRTHDAY GIFT

490
00:18:50,321 --> 00:18:55,660
THEIR HEARTS SWELLED WITH A MIX
OF EMOTIONS DURING THE DREAMY DAY

491
00:18:56,094 --> 00:19:01,633
IT'S TIME THEY DIAL IT BACK
AND RETURN TO REALITY

492
00:19:01,699 --> 00:19:03,067
The day has given me

493
00:19:03,735 --> 00:19:05,536
so much to think about.

494
00:19:05,603 --> 00:19:08,172
WHEN THE EXCITEMENT DIES DOWN

495
00:19:08,239 --> 00:19:12,644
INEXPLICABLE LONELINESS SETTLES IN

496
00:19:13,077 --> 00:19:15,913
I feel so melancholy.

497
00:19:15,980 --> 00:19:18,282
- Same!
- I wasn't the only one?

498
00:19:18,349 --> 00:19:20,284
- You guys feel that way, too?
- Oh, man.

499
00:19:20,351 --> 00:19:22,587
- This is incredible.
- I wasn't sure how to put it.

500
00:19:22,654 --> 00:19:23,688
CAMARADERIE OFF THE CHARTS

501
00:19:23,988 --> 00:19:27,425
It's nothing much,
I feel somewhat melancholy.

502
00:19:27,925 --> 00:19:31,929
I wonder if I'd be able to experience
such feelings again.

503
00:19:31,996 --> 00:19:34,165
Those kinds of thoughts haunt me.

504
00:19:37,068 --> 00:19:38,670
<i>I realized that I've gotten old.</i>

505
00:19:39,404 --> 00:19:40,772
<i>How should I put this?</i>

506
00:19:41,039 --> 00:19:45,043
I learned I'll never feel the way
I did in my twenties.

507
00:19:45,410 --> 00:19:50,481
<i>I sensed that the experiences</i>
<i>I had over the years affected me.</i>

508
00:19:50,548 --> 00:19:53,484
AT AN AGE WHERE THE SENSE OF REALITY
PUTS THE BRAKES ON A RUSH OF EMOTIONS

509
00:19:54,152 --> 00:19:56,554
I feel like we've reached an age

510
00:19:56,621 --> 00:20:02,193
where we clearly know what to pursue
and what to avoid.

511
00:20:02,260 --> 00:20:05,797
But our goal is to realize the dreams
we might otherwise not realize

512
00:20:05,863 --> 00:20:08,199
- Like a catalyst.
- while we're together, right?

513
00:20:08,633 --> 00:20:09,834
You got that right.

514
00:20:10,101 --> 00:20:13,805
Some might've had group dates
back when they turned 20

515
00:20:13,871 --> 00:20:18,242
during their college years,
or during their twenties.

516
00:20:18,309 --> 00:20:22,513
In a sense, I might be feeling regret
about the experiences I missed out.

517
00:20:22,580 --> 00:20:26,551
Or better yet,
the emotional roller coaster rides.

518
00:20:27,218 --> 00:20:29,053
A part of me wants to go back in time

519
00:20:29,120 --> 00:20:33,024
but the other side of me is content
with my current relaxed state.

520
00:20:33,091 --> 00:20:37,662
All these jumbled-up emotions
swallowed the three of us

521
00:20:37,729 --> 00:20:40,164
so our journey home
was silent for some time.

522
00:20:41,466 --> 00:20:42,667
Are you turning on the radio?

523
00:20:43,468 --> 00:20:45,103
Let's see what's on.

524
00:20:45,737 --> 00:20:48,005
- I haven't heard this in a while.
- Whose song is it?

525
00:20:48,372 --> 00:20:50,007
I only remember the title, <i>Mister.</i>

526
00:20:50,074 --> 00:20:51,175
KIM JIN-PYO'S <i>MISTER </i>FROM 2012

527
00:20:52,310 --> 00:20:57,582
IT'S INCREDIBLE HOW EVEN THE RADIO
SEEMS TO BE TELLING THEM THEY'RE OLD

528
00:20:57,648 --> 00:20:59,016
What a coincidence, right?

529
00:20:59,083 --> 00:21:00,485
- Suddenly...
- It's the universe's sign.

530
00:21:00,551 --> 00:21:02,787
THESE OLD MEN ARE OFFENDED

531
00:21:03,354 --> 00:21:04,956
MISTER

532
00:21:05,022 --> 00:21:06,023
THAT SEALED THE DEAL

533
00:21:06,090 --> 00:21:07,725
Guys, but we're not there yet.

534
00:21:07,792 --> 00:21:10,228
- We most definitely are.
- Come on, guys.

535
00:21:10,294 --> 00:21:12,797
You can only be called that way
after you're married.

536
00:21:12,864 --> 00:21:15,366
Isn't it astonishing?
Is the world teasing us?

537
00:21:15,433 --> 00:21:17,168
- You need to get married
- How annoying.

538
00:21:17,235 --> 00:21:19,003
to be called "mister" or "ma'am."

539
00:21:19,070 --> 00:21:21,072
To be honest,
I feel more at ease with the title.

540
00:21:21,139 --> 00:21:23,207
"Uncle" kind of makes me nervous,
but not "mister."

541
00:21:23,474 --> 00:21:25,476
- Really?
- That song had to play just now?

542
00:21:25,777 --> 00:21:28,880
NEXT SONG
EVERYTHING WAS YOU BY NOEL

543
00:21:28,946 --> 00:21:30,982
Out of the blue?

544
00:21:31,549 --> 00:21:35,119
MELANCHOLY ON MULTIPLE LEVELS

545
00:21:36,354 --> 00:21:41,058
THESE THREE OLD MEN
WILL TRY TO BEAR IT, TOO

546
00:21:42,426 --> 00:21:44,595
They probably got home safe, right?

547
00:21:44,662 --> 00:21:46,097
I suppose so.

548
00:21:46,631 --> 00:21:48,699
Why did you go misty-eyed?

549
00:21:48,766 --> 00:21:53,104
I hope they'll remember this day
as a fond memory.

550
00:21:53,738 --> 00:21:54,806
Same.

551
00:21:55,573 --> 00:21:58,843
THIS TRIO IS FEELING SOFT AND MUSHY

552
00:21:58,910 --> 00:22:01,312
HOW IS THE TRIO AT HOME DOING?

553
00:22:02,180 --> 00:22:05,349
THE WIND IS BLOWING FIERCELY
IN GUGI-DONG

554
00:22:06,117 --> 00:22:07,985
You two are just not ready

555
00:22:08,052 --> 00:22:10,221
- to appreciate this show.
- Da-hee.

556
00:22:10,288 --> 00:22:12,790
Hey, you sound like an addict.

557
00:22:12,857 --> 00:22:14,325
Gosh, what do we do?

558
00:22:14,392 --> 00:22:16,160
- Look, there are the husbands.
- The husbands?

559
00:22:16,227 --> 00:22:17,995
- Is that good? Who's on it?
- What is it about?

560
00:22:18,062 --> 00:22:19,897
Isn't it available now?

561
00:22:19,964 --> 00:22:21,799
It only has a notification button.

562
00:22:21,866 --> 00:22:23,201
That startled me.

563
00:22:23,267 --> 00:22:24,936
KYUNG SOO-JIN
LADY GAGA OF GUGI-DONG

564
00:22:25,369 --> 00:22:27,405
LEE DA-HEE
DANIEL'S STERN NANNY

565
00:22:27,705 --> 00:22:29,707
JANG DO-YEON
NEXT-GENERATION MC WITH OCTOPUS

566
00:22:30,775 --> 00:22:32,310
SNORTS

567
00:22:32,376 --> 00:22:33,711
Soo-jin, hold here when you laugh.

568
00:22:34,846 --> 00:22:36,881
- Because the mask won't stay put?
- Yes, of course.

569
00:22:36,948 --> 00:22:38,049
THEY'RE SENSITIVE ABOUT WRINKLES

570
00:22:38,115 --> 00:22:39,183
You know your stuff.

571
00:22:39,250 --> 00:22:40,484
Don't let the upper lip area go dry.

572
00:22:40,551 --> 00:22:41,919
- Good point.
- What a great tip.

573
00:22:42,486 --> 00:22:45,623
FACIAL MASK AND DATING SHOWS
ARE THE GO-TO COMBO FOR GIRLS' TIME

574
00:22:46,357 --> 00:22:48,626
- He likes older women.
- He's got a clear preference.

575
00:22:48,693 --> 00:22:49,760
HOOKED ON A DATING SHOW

576
00:22:49,827 --> 00:22:51,295
He only digs older women.

577
00:22:51,896 --> 00:22:55,032
<i>I don't get much interest</i>
<i>from women my age.</i>

578
00:22:56,067 --> 00:22:58,035
<i>I do get interest</i>
<i>from women advanced in age.</i>

579
00:22:58,102 --> 00:22:59,270
<i>I guess I appeal to them.</i>

580
00:22:59,337 --> 00:23:02,240
Did he just say
"women advanced in age"

581
00:23:02,306 --> 00:23:03,374
instead of just "older women"?

582
00:23:03,441 --> 00:23:06,611
Just how old were they
to be called "advanced in age"?

583
00:23:07,211 --> 00:23:08,946
Do you prefer older men
or younger men?

584
00:23:09,247 --> 00:23:10,648
Younger.

585
00:23:10,948 --> 00:23:12,450
What about you, Da-hee?

586
00:23:14,085 --> 00:23:16,988
I do like older men

587
00:23:17,054 --> 00:23:19,590
but it's getting harder to meet one

588
00:23:19,924 --> 00:23:21,259
every year.

589
00:23:21,325 --> 00:23:22,560
SOLEMN

590
00:23:23,594 --> 00:23:26,063
DESPERATELY HOLDING BACK LAUGHTER
FOR SOME REASON

591
00:23:26,130 --> 00:23:27,265
I like older men.

592
00:23:27,331 --> 00:23:29,500
- Older guys are great.
- I really do.

593
00:23:29,567 --> 00:23:31,168
But it's just

594
00:23:31,235 --> 00:23:33,204
- gotten difficult to meet them.
- I get it.

595
00:23:33,537 --> 00:23:36,073
LOCKING IN ON THE DATING SHOW
AFTER REMOVING THE FACIAL MASKS

596
00:23:36,140 --> 00:23:38,876
<i>You're in the final few years</i>
<i>of the optimal age to get married.</i>

597
00:23:39,210 --> 00:23:41,779
- That's not a real thing.
- Of course not.

598
00:23:41,846 --> 00:23:44,081
- That's right.
- There's no actual period.

599
00:23:44,148 --> 00:23:45,316
The age at which you get married

600
00:23:45,383 --> 00:23:47,084
- is the optimal age for you.
- That's so true.

601
00:23:49,754 --> 00:23:52,023
We grumbled so much
because that hit a raw nerve.

602
00:23:52,089 --> 00:23:53,758
- That hurt, right?
- It struck home.

603
00:23:53,958 --> 00:23:56,160
It hurt so much.

604
00:23:56,227 --> 00:23:58,529
THAT WAS ENOUGH PAIN FOR THE DAY

605
00:23:58,963 --> 00:24:01,465
When do you think
is the optimal age to get married?

606
00:24:03,467 --> 00:24:04,568
It's way behind me.

607
00:24:04,635 --> 00:24:06,103
- You think it's behind you?
- Not really.

608
00:24:06,170 --> 00:24:07,638
Gosh, Do-yeon.

609
00:24:07,705 --> 00:24:09,473
It was nothing.
I was trying to make you laugh.

610
00:24:09,540 --> 00:24:10,574
SOMEHOW SOMBER

611
00:24:10,875 --> 00:24:12,276
- Guys.
- Yeah?

612
00:24:12,810 --> 00:24:14,111
Don't talk that way.

613
00:24:14,445 --> 00:24:15,446
Like what?

614
00:24:16,681 --> 00:24:19,016
We get to choose
our own optimal age to get married.

615
00:24:20,584 --> 00:24:23,821
LET'S BREAK DOWN
THE WORLD'S MISCONCEPTIONS!

616
00:24:25,523 --> 00:24:27,425
- What?
- What on earth?

617
00:24:27,491 --> 00:24:30,661
The moment you get married
is your prime time to get married.

618
00:24:30,728 --> 00:24:32,730
You don't look
like you believe it yourself.

619
00:24:32,797 --> 00:24:33,798
Forget it.

620
00:24:33,864 --> 00:24:37,101
- You didn't even get "guys" right.
- Your pronunciation wasn't clear.

621
00:24:37,168 --> 00:24:39,070
You were doomed
from the moment you spoke.

622
00:24:39,437 --> 00:24:41,072
- Did I mispronounce the word?
- You bet.

623
00:24:41,973 --> 00:24:43,407
Your eyes were already laughing.

624
00:24:43,874 --> 00:24:46,043
Let's suppose
our guys went on this show.

625
00:24:46,110 --> 00:24:48,612
Who do you think
will be the most popular?

626
00:24:49,013 --> 00:24:51,115
I think Jae-hyeon will be popular.

627
00:24:51,182 --> 00:24:53,184
- Of course.
- Jae-hyeon is...

628
00:24:53,617 --> 00:24:54,719
GENTLE AND CARING

629
00:24:54,785 --> 00:24:56,554
<i>He's so considerate.</i>

630
00:24:57,188 --> 00:24:58,689
<i>He will definitely be</i>
<i>the most popular.</i>

631
00:24:58,756 --> 00:25:00,358
<i>Yeah, that's for sure.</i>

632
00:25:00,558 --> 00:25:02,560
Remember how well-dressed
he was earlier?

633
00:25:02,626 --> 00:25:04,562
<i>He had a navy ensemble.</i>

634
00:25:04,628 --> 00:25:06,664
<i>- But it wasn't over-the-top.</i>
<i>- Really?</i>

635
00:25:06,731 --> 00:25:07,765
Just neat.

636
00:25:07,832 --> 00:25:09,767
- What about Keun-suk?
- Keun-suk.

637
00:25:09,834 --> 00:25:11,969
I liked that he dressed down a bit.

638
00:25:12,036 --> 00:25:13,104
Really?

639
00:25:13,838 --> 00:25:15,740
He was dressed a bit
like Bae Yong-joon.

640
00:25:16,240 --> 00:25:17,775
I SEE...

641
00:25:18,042 --> 00:25:20,378
<i>He wore a jacket</i>
<i>and put a long scarf around his neck.</i>

642
00:25:20,444 --> 00:25:23,047
MAYBE THIS IS AS RELAXED
AS THE PRINCE COULD BE?

643
00:25:23,514 --> 00:25:25,116
- What about Daniel?
- Well...

644
00:25:25,182 --> 00:25:26,817
- He went for a preppy look.
- A preppy look?

645
00:25:26,884 --> 00:25:28,285
- He looked like a student rep.
- Really?

646
00:25:28,352 --> 00:25:30,221
- That was the vibe.
- He said he was going for freshman

647
00:25:30,287 --> 00:25:31,856
but he's at the age
of a faculty member.

648
00:25:32,656 --> 00:25:33,657
"Faculty member."

649
00:25:33,724 --> 00:25:35,459
Not even a returning student?

650
00:25:36,627 --> 00:25:38,095
THE THEME CAN'T COMPETE

651
00:25:38,162 --> 00:25:39,997
WITH HIS STRONG MIDDLE-AGED MAN VIBE

652
00:25:40,064 --> 00:25:42,633
If he meets someone
who gets his sense of humor

653
00:25:43,000 --> 00:25:47,171
I think Daniel has a good chance
of getting married.

654
00:25:47,238 --> 00:25:49,073
YOU THINK SO?

655
00:25:49,140 --> 00:25:50,674
He just needs to find
someone compatible.

656
00:25:50,741 --> 00:25:51,876
DA-HEE IS HIS ONLY CHAMPION

657
00:25:52,343 --> 00:25:53,344
<i>I lost almost nine kilograms.</i>

658
00:25:54,245 --> 00:25:57,248
- He must've been a wreck.
- It must've been difficult for him.

659
00:25:57,314 --> 00:25:58,549
To lose that much weight...

660
00:25:58,616 --> 00:26:00,184
ONE PARTICIPANT SAID
HE LOST WEIGHT POST-BREAKUP

661
00:26:04,422 --> 00:26:06,991
- He must've gone through a lot.
- Have you ever experienced that?

662
00:26:08,826 --> 00:26:10,094
I think so.

663
00:26:10,294 --> 00:26:11,996
I have.

664
00:26:12,463 --> 00:26:13,464
When was this?

665
00:26:13,531 --> 00:26:14,799
THESE ARE THEIR LOVE STORIES

666
00:26:15,266 --> 00:26:20,304
It was after I broke up with someone
I had been seeing for a long time.

667
00:26:20,571 --> 00:26:22,773
I honestly couldn't do anything.

668
00:26:25,776 --> 00:26:27,578
We were together
for about three years.

669
00:26:27,645 --> 00:26:30,614
Yes, that sounds about right.
We were together for three years

670
00:26:31,215 --> 00:26:33,651
but he said we should end things.

671
00:26:33,717 --> 00:26:35,486
I clung to him.

672
00:26:35,553 --> 00:26:36,554
- You did?
- Yeah.

673
00:26:36,620 --> 00:26:38,155
- You held him back?
- Yes.

674
00:26:38,956 --> 00:26:39,957
But...

675
00:26:40,958 --> 00:26:42,259
I was in such a bad mood

676
00:26:42,326 --> 00:26:45,196
so my family and I went
on a trip to Ulsan.

677
00:26:45,262 --> 00:26:47,131
I still couldn't do anything there.

678
00:26:47,198 --> 00:26:49,733
That's when I first learned
what heartbreak can do to you.

679
00:26:49,800 --> 00:26:51,302
- Even now, it still...
- It hurts, right?

680
00:26:51,368 --> 00:26:52,670
- My heart hurts.
- Yes.

681
00:26:52,736 --> 00:26:55,439
Somehow, he reached out to me.

682
00:26:55,506 --> 00:26:56,640
So we got back together again.

683
00:26:58,008 --> 00:27:01,345
We had lovely years together

684
00:27:01,812 --> 00:27:03,214
and had a clean break.

685
00:27:03,681 --> 00:27:05,716
Did it hurt less the second time?

686
00:27:05,783 --> 00:27:07,618
It was okay then.

687
00:27:07,685 --> 00:27:09,420
I gave him all the love

688
00:27:09,487 --> 00:27:10,955
- I had to give.
- You had no regrets.

689
00:27:11,021 --> 00:27:12,123
I didn't have regrets.

690
00:27:12,189 --> 00:27:14,058
- You're so like me.
- That was it.

691
00:27:14,125 --> 00:27:16,127
I dated someone for seven years.

692
00:27:17,328 --> 00:27:18,529
A 7-YEAR RELATIONSHIP STORY NEXT

693
00:27:18,596 --> 00:27:21,432
The thing was, I was too young
when I first started seeing him.

694
00:27:22,133 --> 00:27:23,267
So...

695
00:27:23,334 --> 00:27:25,369
I had a strong sense of pride.

696
00:27:25,436 --> 00:27:26,804
- You?
- Yeah.

697
00:27:27,037 --> 00:27:29,340
I hurt my boyfriend at the time.

698
00:27:29,406 --> 00:27:31,342
IN HER IMMATURE DAYS,
SHE HURT HER PARTNER OUT OF PRIDE

699
00:27:31,408 --> 00:27:34,311
And we actually broke up
after a fight.

700
00:27:34,378 --> 00:27:35,379
IN THE END, THEY PARTED WAYS

701
00:27:35,746 --> 00:27:38,549
I thought he would talk me out of it.

702
00:27:38,983 --> 00:27:40,351
But he didn't.

703
00:27:40,985 --> 00:27:43,654
I felt so bad for what I'd done

704
00:27:43,721 --> 00:27:45,589
that I couldn't just let it go.

705
00:27:45,656 --> 00:27:48,392
LEFT HER REGRETFUL
AND UNABLE TO MOVE ON

706
00:27:48,592 --> 00:27:50,561
We did get back together

707
00:27:50,928 --> 00:27:52,263
but a year together was it.

708
00:27:52,329 --> 00:27:53,430
You ended it right away?

709
00:27:53,497 --> 00:27:55,299
- Was it better than?
- I had no regrets then

710
00:27:55,366 --> 00:27:56,734
just like Da-hee.

711
00:27:57,067 --> 00:27:58,569
I gave him my all.

712
00:27:59,036 --> 00:28:00,471
- Only then did I realize
- No regrets, right?

713
00:28:00,538 --> 00:28:02,540
I had broken up without regrets.

714
00:28:02,773 --> 00:28:04,208
Then, it hit me.

715
00:28:04,842 --> 00:28:08,646
"This is how people mature
in relationships."

716
00:28:08,712 --> 00:28:11,582
Before that relationship,
I'd argue for the sake of pride.

717
00:28:11,649 --> 00:28:14,718
But afterward, I was ready
to give my all to the person I loved.

718
00:28:14,785 --> 00:28:17,788
- You're right.
- I think that's how we grow.

719
00:28:18,322 --> 00:28:21,258
ALL RELATIONSHIPS

720
00:28:21,325 --> 00:28:25,262
HELP US MATURE

721
00:28:25,729 --> 00:28:27,097
- We're back.
- What?

722
00:28:28,199 --> 00:28:29,466
THE GUYS ARE BACK FROM THE GROUP DATE

723
00:28:29,533 --> 00:28:31,769
That took pretty long, guys.

724
00:28:31,835 --> 00:28:33,737
EXCITED

725
00:28:33,804 --> 00:28:35,673
We've been dying to know how it went.

726
00:28:36,740 --> 00:28:38,642
- Come on, spill the beans.
- Tell us.

727
00:28:38,709 --> 00:28:39,977
Snap to it.

728
00:28:40,044 --> 00:28:41,045
How did it go?

729
00:28:41,111 --> 00:28:43,514
- You're awfully excited.
- Spill.

730
00:28:43,581 --> 00:28:45,249
- What do you want to know?
- Sit here, Da-hee.

731
00:28:45,316 --> 00:28:46,317
Let the guys sit there.

732
00:28:46,383 --> 00:28:47,418
It's time for your interview.

733
00:28:47,484 --> 00:28:48,619
EXCITEMENT OFF THE CHARTS

734
00:28:49,620 --> 00:28:50,621
But...

735
00:28:50,688 --> 00:28:52,122
BUT THE GUYS SEEM
TO BE FEELING BITTERSWEET

736
00:28:52,189 --> 00:28:53,591
But your expressions are so...

737
00:28:53,657 --> 00:28:55,092
I'm confused.

738
00:28:55,159 --> 00:28:57,361
In one way, they look pleased.

739
00:28:58,095 --> 00:29:00,598
But then again,
they look like defeated soldiers.

740
00:29:00,664 --> 00:29:03,000
DRAINED AND UNRESPONSIVE
EVEN TO A JOKE

741
00:29:03,467 --> 00:29:04,602
Where are you looking at?

742
00:29:04,668 --> 00:29:06,303
- Why do you look so drained?
- What's wrong?

743
00:29:06,370 --> 00:29:07,905
Come on, give us a lively recap.

744
00:29:07,972 --> 00:29:09,373
- We're dying here.
- Seriously.

745
00:29:09,440 --> 00:29:10,975
- Why are you down?
- Why are you so lethargic?

746
00:29:11,041 --> 00:29:15,613
Are you guys all depressed
because the date didn't go well?

747
00:29:17,681 --> 00:29:20,384
I just received a text from Ms. Jung.

748
00:29:21,151 --> 00:29:22,152
What does it say?

749
00:29:22,219 --> 00:29:23,621
Man, this is wild.

750
00:29:23,687 --> 00:29:25,256
- She works fast.
- My gosh.

751
00:29:25,322 --> 00:29:26,323
- I got a text as well.
- What's up?

752
00:29:26,390 --> 00:29:28,292
It shows how many people chose you.

753
00:29:28,359 --> 00:29:29,693
- My goodness.
- For real?

754
00:29:30,094 --> 00:29:31,862
- What?
- What did you guys do?

755
00:29:33,097 --> 00:29:35,266
- For real?
- I just got my text, too.

756
00:29:36,166 --> 00:29:37,368
- Hang on.
- I got my text.

757
00:29:37,434 --> 00:29:39,803
THEY'RE DEFINITELY MORE ANIMATED

758
00:29:39,870 --> 00:29:41,205
So?

759
00:29:41,272 --> 00:29:42,506
How many women chose you?

760
00:29:43,374 --> 00:29:45,609
SO CURIOUS

761
00:29:45,943 --> 00:29:48,045
- I'll read you mine first.
- Kick us off, Jae-hyeon.

762
00:29:48,112 --> 00:29:49,980
THESE TWO ARE STILL READING THEIRS

763
00:29:50,581 --> 00:29:52,216
- "Hello.
- My gosh.

764
00:29:52,283 --> 00:29:54,051
This is the pottery date organizer."

765
00:29:54,585 --> 00:29:55,986
What do we do?

766
00:29:56,053 --> 00:29:58,455
"Shiro, you have been selected...

767
00:29:59,857 --> 00:30:03,093
DID SOMEONE SELECT JAE-HYEON?

768
00:30:04,428 --> 00:30:05,829
...by one person."

769
00:30:05,896 --> 00:30:07,564
1 PERSON SELECTED HIM!

770
00:30:08,065 --> 00:30:10,801
DOES THAT MEAN HE GOT MATCHED?

771
00:30:10,868 --> 00:30:12,036
STARTLED

772
00:30:12,102 --> 00:30:14,772
"Unfortunately,
you were not matched this time.

773
00:30:14,838 --> 00:30:16,874
So your contact info wasn't shared."

774
00:30:17,608 --> 00:30:18,709
MISALIGNED CHOICES

775
00:30:18,776 --> 00:30:21,779
- She doesn't tell you who chose you?
- No.

776
00:30:21,845 --> 00:30:23,514
CHOICES ARE KEPT SECRET
IF A COUPLE ISN'T MATCHED

777
00:30:23,580 --> 00:30:26,684
"If you sign up
for the pottery date again

778
00:30:26,750 --> 00:30:28,419
we offer a discount."

779
00:30:28,485 --> 00:30:30,487
YOU CAN GET A SPECIAL DISCOUNT

780
00:30:30,554 --> 00:30:32,690
- She's good.
- For sure.

781
00:30:32,756 --> 00:30:35,092
- She's great at sales.
- She's terrific.

782
00:30:35,526 --> 00:30:38,262
NEXT HOPE IS ON DANIEL
WHO CHOSE THIS AS A HOUSE SQUAD GOAL

783
00:30:38,762 --> 00:30:39,763
- What's up?
- What's up?

784
00:30:39,830 --> 00:30:40,831
IN UNISON

785
00:30:41,732 --> 00:30:43,967
"Writer Choi of Gugi-dong,
you've been selected

786
00:30:44,034 --> 00:30:45,202
by one person."

787
00:30:45,402 --> 00:30:47,404
They all got chosen.

788
00:30:47,471 --> 00:30:49,039
BUT...

789
00:30:49,406 --> 00:30:52,809
"Unfortunately,
you were not matched this time.

790
00:30:52,876 --> 00:30:54,845
So your contact info wasn't shared."

791
00:30:54,911 --> 00:30:56,179
It's the same as Jae-hyeon's.

792
00:30:56,980 --> 00:30:59,883
Same here. "AP,
you've been selected by one person."

793
00:30:59,950 --> 00:31:01,785
CHOSEN BUT UNMATCHED

794
00:31:01,852 --> 00:31:04,254
- So your crush chose someone else?
- That's right.

795
00:31:04,321 --> 00:31:05,922
- Exactly.
- If the interest isn't mutual...

796
00:31:05,989 --> 00:31:08,692
We're unmatched because the one
I chose didn't choose me.

797
00:31:08,759 --> 00:31:10,293
Is that how it works?

798
00:31:10,360 --> 00:31:12,896
It'd mean that everyone chose
someone who didn't choose them.

799
00:31:13,930 --> 00:31:15,198
GAZING FIXEDLY

800
00:31:15,298 --> 00:31:17,134
This is unexpectedly bitter.

801
00:31:17,901 --> 00:31:19,903
No, I had a really good time.

802
00:31:20,837 --> 00:31:23,507
It's been so long
since I last heard excited giggles.

803
00:31:23,573 --> 00:31:24,708
NEWFOUND ROMANTIC FEELINGS

804
00:31:24,775 --> 00:31:27,444
You rarely get to talk to people
from different industries.

805
00:31:27,511 --> 00:31:29,312
That alone was pretty unique.

806
00:31:29,379 --> 00:31:30,647
MEANINGFUL ON ITS OWN

807
00:31:31,048 --> 00:31:33,517
- I bet it feels good to be chosen.
- I know.

808
00:31:33,583 --> 00:31:35,152
- You guys got chosen.
- You all did.

809
00:31:35,218 --> 00:31:36,920
- Better than zero, right?
- Sure.

810
00:31:36,987 --> 00:31:37,988
Still...

811
00:31:38,488 --> 00:31:40,057
- It's a bit disappointing, though.
- Yes.

812
00:31:42,626 --> 00:31:45,629
FOR SOME REASON

813
00:31:45,696 --> 00:31:48,732
HIS GAZE REMAINS FIXED ON ONE PERSON

814
00:31:49,666 --> 00:31:51,168
What's wrong with them?

815
00:31:53,770 --> 00:31:55,138
I just thought

816
00:31:55,205 --> 00:31:57,340
about how much I missed you guys

817
00:31:57,407 --> 00:31:58,675
before our dates arrived.

818
00:31:59,242 --> 00:32:01,044
- I missed you, and I was so nervous.
- Us?

819
00:32:01,111 --> 00:32:03,213
- Really?
- The nerves made me think...

820
00:32:03,280 --> 00:32:04,548
Don't talk nonsense.

821
00:32:05,415 --> 00:32:06,416
No, I mean it.

822
00:32:06,483 --> 00:32:09,186
I feel at ease around you guys,
and you're so dependable.

823
00:32:09,786 --> 00:32:11,755
- He's not lying.
- Really?

824
00:32:11,822 --> 00:32:12,823
Yeah.

825
00:32:12,889 --> 00:32:14,291
YET AGAIN

826
00:32:14,357 --> 00:32:19,196
SILENCE FALLS

827
00:32:19,463 --> 00:32:21,998
HOW DO WE SALVAGE THIS?

828
00:32:22,432 --> 00:32:24,668
SOO-JIN DECIDES
TO USE HER SECRET WEAPON

829
00:32:24,735 --> 00:32:26,236
- We danced yesterday.
- The dance lesson?

830
00:32:26,303 --> 00:32:27,804
- We shot videos, too.
- Really?

831
00:32:27,871 --> 00:32:29,806
Let's show them to these guys.

832
00:32:29,873 --> 00:32:31,875
- Please don't.
- Come on.

833
00:32:31,942 --> 00:32:33,777
You have the videos?

834
00:32:34,411 --> 00:32:36,046
- What is it?
- Let's watch together.

835
00:32:36,480 --> 00:32:38,849
- So...
- Watch by yourselves.

836
00:32:38,915 --> 00:32:41,051
- The final cut.
- I feel like throwing up.

837
00:32:41,818 --> 00:32:42,953
- Here's Do-yeon's.
- Do-yeon.

838
00:32:43,587 --> 00:32:45,021
- Do-yeon.
- She's a good dancer.

839
00:32:45,088 --> 00:32:46,456
- What the heck?
- Wow!

840
00:32:46,523 --> 00:32:47,724
- Oh, man!
- What's this?

841
00:32:47,791 --> 00:32:49,192
So neat!

842
00:32:49,259 --> 00:32:50,260
Let's go.

843
00:32:50,327 --> 00:32:51,561
<i>Play the music.</i>

844
00:32:55,098 --> 00:32:58,235
CRACKING UP

845
00:32:58,602 --> 00:33:02,405
BURSTING INTO LAUGHTER
AT THEIR HOUSEMATE'S MOVES

846
00:33:02,873 --> 00:33:03,974
Hey, she's blushing.

847
00:33:04,040 --> 00:33:05,842
- She's getting redder.
- She's barely holding back.

848
00:33:05,909 --> 00:33:07,978
- She's all flushed.
- She's hanging on.

849
00:33:08,044 --> 00:33:09,312
- What?
- A reality check, I bet.

850
00:33:09,813 --> 00:33:10,914
Her energy...

851
00:33:10,981 --> 00:33:13,383
THANKS TO THE CONSIDERATE GIRL PALS

852
00:33:13,450 --> 00:33:17,854
THE GUYS COULD LAUGH AGAIN

853
00:33:17,921 --> 00:33:19,222
That's her signature move.

854
00:33:19,756 --> 00:33:21,825
THEY'RE FINALLY LAUGHING

855
00:33:22,259 --> 00:33:24,094
THIS IS HOW GUGI-DONG FAM
CONSOLES ONE ANOTHER

856
00:33:24,161 --> 00:33:25,362
That's a great finish.

857
00:33:25,929 --> 00:33:26,930
So fierce, right?

858
00:33:27,430 --> 00:33:28,698
She's got great moves.

859
00:33:28,765 --> 00:33:30,167
- Right?
- Yes.

860
00:33:30,934 --> 00:33:32,736
- Where did Do-yeon go?
- Let's go.

861
00:33:32,803 --> 00:33:33,804
Is she getting ready?

862
00:33:34,371 --> 00:33:36,540
Let's get ready now.

863
00:33:36,606 --> 00:33:38,041
<i>Hey, Do-yeon.</i>

864
00:33:38,942 --> 00:33:40,410
<i>- She's getting ready.</i>
<i>- Yeah.</i>

865
00:33:40,477 --> 00:33:42,612
- We'll get ready!
- Okay.

866
00:33:42,679 --> 00:33:45,015
When do we slow dance
if we do get to do it?

867
00:33:45,081 --> 00:33:46,149
On my birthday.

868
00:33:46,216 --> 00:33:50,387
We'd have to be dressed up
for the special occasion.

869
00:33:50,620 --> 00:33:52,989
Oh, AP.

870
00:33:53,056 --> 00:33:54,691
You look so fine.

871
00:33:54,758 --> 00:33:56,226
That's me pushing myself forward.

872
00:33:56,293 --> 00:33:57,727
- Isn't that Soo-jin?
- My gosh.

873
00:33:57,794 --> 00:33:59,262
What?

874
00:33:59,462 --> 00:34:01,765
<i>- Doesn't it match the occasion?</i>
<i>- You look so different.</i>

875
00:34:01,832 --> 00:34:03,033
<i>Doesn't this match the dress code?</i>

876
00:34:03,099 --> 00:34:05,468
<i>It feels so strange</i>

877
00:34:06,069 --> 00:34:07,070
<i>to be dressed up like this.</i>

878
00:34:09,739 --> 00:34:10,740
What?

879
00:34:10,807 --> 00:34:12,008
WELCOME

880
00:34:12,075 --> 00:34:13,143
- What's all this?
- Oh, man.

881
00:34:13,210 --> 00:34:14,644
Come on in, then.

882
00:34:15,045 --> 00:34:16,379
- Shall we, then?
- Yeah.

883
00:34:18,348 --> 00:34:20,784
LOOKING SLEEK
IN HIS FIRST-EVER BESPOKE SUIT

884
00:34:20,851 --> 00:34:22,285
<i>So this is what it looks like.</i>

885
00:34:22,919 --> 00:34:26,857
TROUBLEMAKER MODE, OFF
LEADING MAN MODE, ON

886
00:34:28,124 --> 00:34:29,659
<i>He's a prince in real life.</i>

887
00:34:29,726 --> 00:34:31,962
DUMMY MODE, OFF
PRINCE MODE, ON

888
00:34:33,129 --> 00:34:37,901
AHN-GEL MODE, OFF
ALPHA MALE MODE, ON

889
00:34:37,968 --> 00:34:41,638
STERN NANNY MODE, OFF
LOVELY LADY MODE, ON

890
00:34:42,239 --> 00:34:45,642
INTROVERT MODE, OFF
BUSINESS MODE, ON

891
00:34:46,810 --> 00:34:50,881
ALPHA GIRL MODE, OFF
UNEXPECTED CHARM, ON

892
00:34:51,715 --> 00:34:52,849
- Hello.
- Hello.

893
00:34:52,916 --> 00:34:55,085
HOMEBODY MODE, OFF
DRESSED-UP MODE, ON

894
00:34:55,151 --> 00:34:56,453
- Do you have a reservation?
- Yes.

895
00:34:56,519 --> 00:34:58,255
- It's under Choi Daniel.
- Okay.

896
00:34:58,555 --> 00:35:00,423
- Just a second. I'll check for you.
- Of course.

897
00:35:00,924 --> 00:35:02,559
- This way, please.
- Okay.

898
00:35:02,626 --> 00:35:04,561
STIFF AND FORCED

899
00:35:04,828 --> 00:35:06,897
They have a piano here.
Can you believe it?

900
00:35:07,397 --> 00:35:09,132
It's a grand piano, at that.

901
00:35:09,199 --> 00:35:10,233
SPECIAL REASON BEHIND THE PICK

902
00:35:11,001 --> 00:35:15,438
MUST-HAVE ITEMS FOR SLOW DANCING
A GRAND PIANO

903
00:35:15,505 --> 00:35:18,308
AND A SPACIOUS STAGE

904
00:35:19,309 --> 00:35:20,844
MOVIE OF DANIEL'S DREAM,
<i>SCENT OF A WOMAN</i>

905
00:35:20,911 --> 00:35:22,078
How lovely.

906
00:35:22,712 --> 00:35:24,414
Take a seat, guys.

907
00:35:24,481 --> 00:35:25,548
How should we sit?

908
00:35:25,615 --> 00:35:27,284
HE DECIDED TO SPURGE
AND BOOKED THIS RESTAURANT

909
00:35:27,350 --> 00:35:29,419
We can just sit like this.

910
00:35:29,986 --> 00:35:32,022
It feels awkward for me, too.

911
00:35:33,056 --> 00:35:34,057
Hello.

912
00:35:35,225 --> 00:35:36,226
Hello.

913
00:35:39,696 --> 00:35:40,697
Okay.

914
00:35:41,131 --> 00:35:44,601
THE UNEXPECTED FOREIGN BOSS

915
00:35:44,668 --> 00:35:45,669
Okay.

916
00:35:46,469 --> 00:35:47,470
Okay.

917
00:35:47,537 --> 00:35:49,406
THIS WASN'T PART OF MY PLAN

918
00:35:49,472 --> 00:35:50,473
I see.

919
00:35:51,141 --> 00:35:54,644
FORGET SLOW DANCING,
ORDERING FOOD IS ALREADY A CHALLENGE

920
00:35:54,711 --> 00:35:55,712
I see.

921
00:35:55,779 --> 00:35:57,480
STARING BLANKLY

922
00:35:58,048 --> 00:36:00,417
STARING INTO SPACE

923
00:36:00,917 --> 00:36:02,919
I'm hyped.

924
00:36:04,054 --> 00:36:05,055
Thank you.

925
00:36:05,121 --> 00:36:07,590
THEY ONLY GOT THE LAST PART
AND THE RECOMMENDATIONS WERE OVER

926
00:36:07,924 --> 00:36:09,893
You guys have been learning English,
Do-yeon and Soo-jin.

927
00:36:09,960 --> 00:36:12,829
He said they have great dishes
and promised to get us the finest.

928
00:36:16,132 --> 00:36:18,234
AWKWARD

929
00:36:18,301 --> 00:36:20,403
RESTLESS

930
00:36:20,470 --> 00:36:23,306
- It's just...
- It feels so awkward to be here.

931
00:36:23,373 --> 00:36:25,675
- We've been relaxed this whole time.
- Yeah, it's a bit...

932
00:36:25,742 --> 00:36:28,345
Don't we have some curry
left in the fridge?

933
00:36:28,411 --> 00:36:30,480
- We have short ribs, too.
- I keep thinking about them.

934
00:36:30,547 --> 00:36:32,849
I thought about them
just on our way up here.

935
00:36:32,916 --> 00:36:34,718
LAUGHING

936
00:36:34,784 --> 00:36:37,053
- Should we study the menu?
- Let's place an order.

937
00:36:37,120 --> 00:36:38,488
- Let's make an order.
- All right.

938
00:36:38,955 --> 00:36:39,956
Okay.

939
00:36:40,023 --> 00:36:41,291
I think pizzas will be good here.

940
00:36:41,358 --> 00:36:42,425
- Good idea.
- They look good.

941
00:36:43,493 --> 00:36:44,928
Should I call him now?

942
00:36:45,996 --> 00:36:47,864
Are there service bells here?

943
00:36:47,931 --> 00:36:49,833
- We'll have to raise our hand.
- Like this?

944
00:36:50,367 --> 00:36:52,235
- Just the gesture.
- You sure?

945
00:36:54,004 --> 00:36:56,139
- You sure?
- Or maybe eye contact?

946
00:36:56,206 --> 00:36:57,941
- Let's see.
- Okay, Daniel.

947
00:36:58,008 --> 00:36:59,642
- He's here.
- We're in trouble.

948
00:36:59,709 --> 00:37:01,244
He's coming. We're in trouble.

949
00:37:05,315 --> 00:37:06,483
Can I take your order?

950
00:37:08,051 --> 00:37:09,052
Oh, great.

951
00:37:09,119 --> 00:37:11,121
Why didn't you come to us earlier?

952
00:37:11,187 --> 00:37:12,555
My apologies.

953
00:37:12,622 --> 00:37:15,525
This section here
covers our appetizers.

954
00:37:15,592 --> 00:37:18,428
DEEP IN THOUGHT

955
00:37:18,495 --> 00:37:19,496
Pardon my interruption.

956
00:37:19,562 --> 00:37:21,231
- But it's someone's birthday today.
- Yes?

957
00:37:21,631 --> 00:37:23,967
ME?

958
00:37:24,167 --> 00:37:25,802
- Yes?
- Do you offer special services?

959
00:37:25,869 --> 00:37:27,203
A PURE QUESTION

960
00:37:27,270 --> 00:37:28,371
We haven't even ordered yet.

961
00:37:28,571 --> 00:37:30,807
- That's not necessary.
- If you order a dessert

962
00:37:30,874 --> 00:37:32,242
- we'll write a message.
- A dessert?

963
00:37:32,308 --> 00:37:33,576
A message.

964
00:37:33,643 --> 00:37:35,078
A message decoration.

965
00:37:35,145 --> 00:37:36,913
SOMEWHAT EMBARRASSED

966
00:37:36,980 --> 00:37:38,248
A message.

967
00:37:38,314 --> 00:37:39,516
A message decoration.

968
00:37:39,849 --> 00:37:41,684
That can be meaningful.

969
00:37:41,751 --> 00:37:43,420
Good job.

970
00:37:43,486 --> 00:37:44,754
Right?

971
00:37:44,821 --> 00:37:45,889
You're smart.

972
00:37:45,955 --> 00:37:49,459
Can we get all the signature dishes?

973
00:37:49,526 --> 00:37:50,760
Of course.

974
00:37:50,827 --> 00:37:51,961
- Great.
- Thank you.

975
00:37:52,028 --> 00:37:53,029
- Of course.
- Thank you.

976
00:37:53,096 --> 00:37:54,397
- Thank you.
- Great.

977
00:37:54,464 --> 00:37:56,633
You ordered all the signature dishes.

978
00:37:56,699 --> 00:37:57,801
That does make you feel easy.

979
00:37:58,068 --> 00:38:00,003
Since it's my birthday

980
00:38:00,070 --> 00:38:03,139
- I want us to share good food.
- Love the idea.

981
00:38:03,206 --> 00:38:05,108
- I thought...
- Is it your treat?

982
00:38:05,175 --> 00:38:06,743
- Sure.
- My goodness.

983
00:38:06,976 --> 00:38:08,078
I'm excited.

984
00:38:09,813 --> 00:38:13,883
- But this place is really grand.
- Did you rent the entire place?

985
00:38:13,950 --> 00:38:15,919
Did you rent the entire place?

986
00:38:15,985 --> 00:38:18,121
No, I merely made a reservation.

987
00:38:19,122 --> 00:38:20,557
Goodness.

988
00:38:20,623 --> 00:38:21,758
Look at the ceiling.

989
00:38:21,825 --> 00:38:22,992
It's so glamorous.

990
00:38:23,059 --> 00:38:24,761
IT WILL BE BETTER THIS WAY
TO SLOW DANCE LATER

991
00:38:25,195 --> 00:38:27,797
Look at you, all dressed up.

992
00:38:28,331 --> 00:38:29,666
You all clean up nicely.

993
00:38:30,600 --> 00:38:32,635
- It feels strange, actually.
- Me too.

994
00:38:33,236 --> 00:38:35,338
Just moments ago, we were in sweats.

995
00:38:36,406 --> 00:38:41,478
THEY'VE SEEN EACH OTHER
AT THEIR MOST RELAXED STATE SO FAR

996
00:38:42,278 --> 00:38:44,547
ESPECIALLY THE MAN OF THE DAY

997
00:38:44,614 --> 00:38:47,016
WHO ARE YOU?

998
00:38:47,750 --> 00:38:49,018
HOW CAN IT BE THIS AWKWARD?

999
00:38:49,085 --> 00:38:51,020
I'm getting pen-pricking sensations
in my stomach.

1000
00:38:51,087 --> 00:38:52,755
- What?
- I can't get used to this vibe.

1001
00:38:52,822 --> 00:38:53,823
Same here.

1002
00:38:53,890 --> 00:38:55,959
We've been staying
far too relaxed so far.

1003
00:38:56,025 --> 00:38:57,827
- I know.
- And now, we're all glammed up.

1004
00:38:57,894 --> 00:38:59,462
My body is having trouble adjusting.

1005
00:38:59,529 --> 00:39:01,097
You had a little bun up here earlier.

1006
00:39:01,164 --> 00:39:02,265
- Right.
- Just a few moments ago.

1007
00:39:02,332 --> 00:39:03,800
My hair is all brushed neatly.

1008
00:39:03,867 --> 00:39:06,669
I almost feel like a cat
forced to wear a costume.

1009
00:39:06,736 --> 00:39:09,672
I was thinking that you looked
the most natural here.

1010
00:39:09,739 --> 00:39:11,407
You're blending in perfectly.

1011
00:39:11,474 --> 00:39:12,909
Don't I look stiff, though?

1012
00:39:12,976 --> 00:39:14,677
- I can't move.
- He does look stiff.

1013
00:39:14,744 --> 00:39:15,745
Really?

1014
00:39:16,412 --> 00:39:18,648
So what do you think
about your activity-packed birthday?

1015
00:39:18,715 --> 00:39:20,016
- Are you enjoying it?
- Honestly

1016
00:39:20,517 --> 00:39:22,552
- I feel energized.
- You do?

1017
00:39:22,619 --> 00:39:25,188
Have you ever had
a fancy birthday party before?

1018
00:39:25,255 --> 00:39:26,789
One with a dress code?

1019
00:39:26,856 --> 00:39:27,924
This is the first time.

1020
00:39:28,424 --> 00:39:30,793
I've never had events
with dress codes before.

1021
00:39:31,461 --> 00:39:32,629
I'm sure that's clear to you now.

1022
00:39:33,563 --> 00:39:38,301
HE GOT HIS FIRST-EVER BESPOKE SUIT
FOR HIS FIRST HOUSE SQUAD GOAL

1023
00:39:38,368 --> 00:39:39,969
AND HE'S WEARING IT
FOR HIS 40TH BIRTHDAY

1024
00:39:40,036 --> 00:39:41,738
I just got this for my birthday...

1025
00:39:41,804 --> 00:39:43,206
- And you look amazing.
- You're the star.

1026
00:39:43,273 --> 00:39:44,574
- You look impressive.
- I do?

1027
00:39:44,641 --> 00:39:46,209
- In that black suit.
- You look hot

1028
00:39:46,276 --> 00:39:47,577
- in that color.
- Told you, right?

1029
00:39:47,977 --> 00:39:49,612
You're the star.

1030
00:39:49,679 --> 00:39:50,813
For sure.

1031
00:39:51,080 --> 00:39:52,115
Really?

1032
00:39:52,182 --> 00:39:53,216
HIS HEART FLUTTERS

1033
00:39:53,650 --> 00:39:55,418
BIRTHDAYS ROCK

1034
00:39:56,052 --> 00:39:58,421
CAN YOU BELIEVE HOW HAPPY HE IS?

1035
00:39:58,488 --> 00:39:59,489
Shall we have a toast?

1036
00:39:59,556 --> 00:40:00,957
- Sure.
- Yeah, let's do that.

1037
00:40:01,024 --> 00:40:03,026
- Happy birthday, Daniel.
- Thank you.

1038
00:40:03,092 --> 00:40:04,294
- Congrats.
- Congrats.

1039
00:40:04,360 --> 00:40:05,628
Thank you.

1040
00:40:06,763 --> 00:40:08,331
THIS TEETOTALER DRINKS WATER INSTEAD

1041
00:40:08,398 --> 00:40:09,799
Nice and cool.

1042
00:40:09,866 --> 00:40:11,134
- It's good.
- Right?

1043
00:40:11,367 --> 00:40:13,303
I wonder where the ladies' room is.

1044
00:40:13,369 --> 00:40:16,306
- Go outside and turn right.
- Turn right over there?

1045
00:40:16,372 --> 00:40:17,674
Yeah, that's it.

1046
00:40:17,740 --> 00:40:20,043
SOO-JIN HEADS TO THE LADIES' ROOM
WHILE HUMMING

1047
00:40:20,343 --> 00:40:21,544
Should we have some bread?

1048
00:40:21,611 --> 00:40:23,213
- Let's have a bite.
- Looks great.

1049
00:40:24,214 --> 00:40:25,215
My gosh.

1050
00:40:27,917 --> 00:40:29,319
- What?
- Look at you.

1051
00:40:29,385 --> 00:40:31,054
My gosh!

1052
00:40:31,654 --> 00:40:34,557
ALL EYES ON HER RED DRESS

1053
00:40:35,592 --> 00:40:36,926
Look at our red goddess.

1054
00:40:36,993 --> 00:40:39,429
UNLEASHING HER RED GODDESS LOOK
THAT WAS HIDDEN BENEATH THE COAT

1055
00:40:39,495 --> 00:40:41,231
- Look at you.
- My gosh!

1056
00:40:41,297 --> 00:40:43,166
THIS ISN'T THE SOO-JIN
THAT WE'RE USED TO!

1057
00:40:43,233 --> 00:40:45,034
- Did we get our bread basket?
- Look at our red goddess.

1058
00:40:45,101 --> 00:40:47,303
Your dress fits perfectly here.

1059
00:40:47,370 --> 00:40:49,639
- You look like you own the place.
- Yeah, you really do.

1060
00:40:50,006 --> 00:40:51,808
ABSOLUTELY MESMERIZING

1061
00:40:54,310 --> 00:40:55,445
You look different, Soo-jin.

1062
00:40:55,511 --> 00:40:57,880
You look like an entrepreneur
who made it big early.

1063
00:40:57,947 --> 00:41:01,351
- Maybe the CEO of this place?
- You look like you own the place.

1064
00:41:01,851 --> 00:41:04,087
Order whatever you'd like.
It's my treat.

1065
00:41:04,787 --> 00:41:05,955
It doesn't cost a penny to say it.

1066
00:41:06,189 --> 00:41:07,423
You look different.

1067
00:41:08,758 --> 00:41:11,027
STARING FIXEDLY

1068
00:41:11,094 --> 00:41:13,663
The dominant image
I've had of you so far has been

1069
00:41:13,730 --> 00:41:16,699
when you had a towel around your head
and tried to hold this pose.

1070
00:41:16,766 --> 00:41:18,368
"This is what I'm talking about."

1071
00:41:19,802 --> 00:41:23,673
THIS IS THE HOUSEMATE WE REMEMBER

1072
00:41:24,073 --> 00:41:27,410
OUR HOUSEMATE HAS CHANGED

1073
00:41:28,044 --> 00:41:32,315
I might've fallen for you
if we had met like this.

1074
00:41:32,382 --> 00:41:33,716
- The way you are now.
- Really?

1075
00:41:37,120 --> 00:41:39,455
- You look so beautiful.
- She sure does.

1076
00:41:40,156 --> 00:41:41,624
But then again

1077
00:41:41,691 --> 00:41:44,060
considering the days
we've spent together

1078
00:41:44,127 --> 00:41:45,228
I can't fall for you now.

1079
00:41:45,295 --> 00:41:47,096
CHANGING THE MESSAGE
THIS WAY AND THAT ALL ALONE

1080
00:41:50,767 --> 00:41:53,069
- "I can't fall for you now"?
- Our loyalty would prevent that.

1081
00:41:53,736 --> 00:41:55,638
- Let's just chug it down.
- Okay.

1082
00:41:56,205 --> 00:41:57,206
0 CONFESSION, 1 REJECTION

1083
00:41:57,273 --> 00:41:58,875
How classy.

1084
00:41:58,941 --> 00:41:59,942
Happy birthday.

1085
00:42:00,009 --> 00:42:01,511
- Thanks.
- Happy birthday.

1086
00:42:01,577 --> 00:42:03,680
AS THEY RAISE GLASSES TOGETHER
WITH A GENEROUS HEART

1087
00:42:05,915 --> 00:42:07,684
- Unbelievable.
- We've got our meal.

1088
00:42:07,750 --> 00:42:09,519
- Wow, thank you.
- Thank you.

1089
00:42:10,153 --> 00:42:11,954
<i>Here's the pizza</i>
<i>Keun-suk has been waiting for.</i>

1090
00:42:12,021 --> 00:42:13,756
<i>- Enjoy.</i>
<i>- That's </i>Vongole, <i>right?</i>

1091
00:42:13,823 --> 00:42:15,792
AN ELEGANT SPECIAL FEAST
FOR DANIEL'S 40TH BIRTHDAY

1092
00:42:15,858 --> 00:42:17,160
<i>My gosh.</i>

1093
00:42:18,361 --> 00:42:20,129
- Do you want some pizza, Do-yeon?
- Pizza.

1094
00:42:20,196 --> 00:42:21,464
- One slice, then.
- How about <i>jamón?</i>

1095
00:42:21,531 --> 00:42:22,532
You want some <i>jamón?</i>

1096
00:42:22,999 --> 00:42:24,434
Take all this arugula, too.

1097
00:42:24,500 --> 00:42:25,735
Great. Thanks.

1098
00:42:27,470 --> 00:42:28,771
- Jae-hyeon.
- Yes, Daniel?

1099
00:42:28,838 --> 00:42:29,839
PLAYING THE ROLE OF A FATHER

1100
00:42:29,906 --> 00:42:31,040
This looks amazing.

1101
00:42:31,974 --> 00:42:33,609
- That's lasagna.
- Thanks.

1102
00:42:33,876 --> 00:42:35,411
I'm loving the <i>jamón.</i>

1103
00:42:35,478 --> 00:42:37,113
My gosh.

1104
00:42:37,780 --> 00:42:39,982
- So? Is it incredible?
- Sure.

1105
00:42:40,049 --> 00:42:41,217
It's so good.

1106
00:42:41,284 --> 00:42:42,552
- It's amazing.
- Yeah.

1107
00:42:43,986 --> 00:42:45,888
THAT'S THE FACE
A PROUD FATHER WOULD MAKE

1108
00:42:45,955 --> 00:42:46,956
Hey, this is delicious.

1109
00:42:47,023 --> 00:42:48,358
- It's good.
- It's seasoned just right.

1110
00:42:48,424 --> 00:42:49,959
Not too salty. Just right.

1111
00:42:50,660 --> 00:42:51,794
EXPERTLY SITTING DOWN

1112
00:42:51,861 --> 00:42:53,663
Every second feels so precious.

1113
00:42:53,730 --> 00:42:55,965
I know. I've never had...

1114
00:42:56,032 --> 00:42:57,400
He's going to play the piano.

1115
00:42:58,201 --> 00:42:59,702
It's the owner.

1116
00:42:59,769 --> 00:43:02,004
THE OWNER IS THE PIANIST HERE!

1117
00:43:02,071 --> 00:43:03,940
He's so awesome.

1118
00:43:04,006 --> 00:43:05,908
Way to go, Mr. Owner.

1119
00:43:05,975 --> 00:43:07,477
The live background music

1120
00:43:07,543 --> 00:43:09,045
- definitely enhances the vibe.
- Yeah.

1121
00:43:09,112 --> 00:43:11,514
- That's true.
- It was too quiet earlier.

1122
00:43:11,748 --> 00:43:13,449
- It helps you relax, right?
- Yeah.

1123
00:43:13,516 --> 00:43:14,684
I feel more at ease.

1124
00:43:15,218 --> 00:43:17,854
A SPACE JUST FOR US

1125
00:43:18,654 --> 00:43:20,790
WITH THE MELLOW MUSIC
IN THE BACKGROUND

1126
00:43:20,857 --> 00:43:23,092
GREAT FOOD ON THE TABLE

1127
00:43:23,693 --> 00:43:27,029
AND THE DEAR FAM BY MY SIDE

1128
00:43:27,096 --> 00:43:28,431
So wild.

1129
00:43:28,498 --> 00:43:31,267
THE ONLY THING MY 40TH BIRTHDAY NEEDS

1130
00:43:31,334 --> 00:43:34,871
IS THE SLOW DANCE

1131
00:43:35,405 --> 00:43:37,173
We've got more guests.

1132
00:43:37,473 --> 00:43:39,008
No way.

1133
00:43:39,075 --> 00:43:40,710
We've got more guests.

1134
00:43:40,777 --> 00:43:42,779
- What?
- No way.

1135
00:43:42,845 --> 00:43:43,980
FILMED WITH THE GUESTS' CONSENT

1136
00:43:44,046 --> 00:43:45,948
- My gosh.
- It's a group of foreigners.

1137
00:43:46,015 --> 00:43:48,451
Are they the owner's friends?
What's going on?

1138
00:43:48,518 --> 00:43:49,585
Seriously, what is all this?

1139
00:43:50,420 --> 00:43:53,589
- Is this for real?
- What do we do?

1140
00:43:55,024 --> 00:43:57,994
Are they going to sit
at a table near us?

1141
00:43:58,060 --> 00:43:59,729
Let me order some more beer.

1142
00:43:59,796 --> 00:44:00,830
Hold on.

1143
00:44:00,897 --> 00:44:02,965
My back hurts from laughing so much.

1144
00:44:03,032 --> 00:44:05,101
CAN THEY SLOW DANCE
WITH THESE PEOPLE PRESENT?

1145
00:44:05,802 --> 00:44:08,638
Maybe I should get
a glass of wine or two.

1146
00:44:08,704 --> 00:44:09,972
SHAKING LIKE A LEAF

1147
00:44:13,209 --> 00:44:16,379
THE 1ST SESSION OF LIVE MUSIC
COMES TO AN END

1148
00:44:17,346 --> 00:44:18,981
- Great.
- Great.

1149
00:44:19,048 --> 00:44:20,716
GRANDE MEANS "GREAT" IN ITALIAN

1150
00:44:20,783 --> 00:44:23,453
- Wonderful.
- Great.

1151
00:44:24,454 --> 00:44:26,956
Hey, Daniel.
About your House Squad Goal.

1152
00:44:27,023 --> 00:44:28,524
Will you really be dancing later?

1153
00:44:29,225 --> 00:44:31,160
Yes, that was the plan.

1154
00:44:32,195 --> 00:44:33,863
To be honest

1155
00:44:34,497 --> 00:44:38,968
I do have one project
I've been carrying close to my heart.

1156
00:44:39,035 --> 00:44:40,236
- What is it?
- What?

1157
00:44:40,303 --> 00:44:41,771
I never shared this with anyone.

1158
00:44:41,838 --> 00:44:43,105
What is it?

1159
00:44:43,172 --> 00:44:45,741
One thing I want to try is...

1160
00:44:47,376 --> 00:44:51,113
to examine
the realistic options for a wedding.

1161
00:44:53,583 --> 00:44:56,385
I want to visit a wedding hall

1162
00:44:56,886 --> 00:44:59,555
- A wedding hall?
- to compare my dream wedding

1163
00:44:59,622 --> 00:45:01,791
with the actual ceremonies
offered at the venue.

1164
00:45:01,858 --> 00:45:03,526
I want to get a quote, too.

1165
00:45:03,593 --> 00:45:04,794
A WEDDING PLANNER'S CONSULTATION?

1166
00:45:04,861 --> 00:45:07,230
You want a consultation
from a wedding planner?

1167
00:45:07,296 --> 00:45:09,031
I'd like to check everything

1168
00:45:09,098 --> 00:45:10,933
from flowers
to our walk on the aisle.

1169
00:45:11,000 --> 00:45:12,735
What kind of music should be played

1170
00:45:12,802 --> 00:45:14,670
when I first enter the hall,
for instance?

1171
00:45:15,471 --> 00:45:17,073
You've really thought things out,
haven't you?

1172
00:45:17,139 --> 00:45:19,642
I'm really startled
by your detailed ideas.

1173
00:45:20,076 --> 00:45:23,312
Are you exploring options
because marriage is on the horizon?

1174
00:45:23,379 --> 00:45:25,114
- It's pure research.
- For no specific reason?

1175
00:45:25,181 --> 00:45:26,482
I'm the only one staying single

1176
00:45:26,549 --> 00:45:28,985
when most of my friends
have already gotten married.

1177
00:45:29,051 --> 00:45:31,120
I've wanted to see how it is.

1178
00:45:31,187 --> 00:45:33,289
I was considering going tomorrow.

1179
00:45:33,356 --> 00:45:37,527
"Now I've reached the age
where I shouldn't be running away."

1180
00:45:37,593 --> 00:45:40,963
That thought has been
creeping up on me.

1181
00:45:41,197 --> 00:45:43,432
Rather than making a joke out of it

1182
00:45:43,499 --> 00:45:46,936
it's time I gave it serious thought.

1183
00:45:48,037 --> 00:45:49,038
- Really?
- So

1184
00:45:49,105 --> 00:45:51,707
if any of you are available
for a consultation tomorrow...

1185
00:45:51,774 --> 00:45:53,175
- I'll come with you.
- Are you free?

1186
00:45:53,242 --> 00:45:54,343
I'm up for it.

1187
00:45:54,410 --> 00:45:56,245
- I've been curious, too.
- I didn't want to go alone

1188
00:45:56,312 --> 00:45:57,813
because couples usually go together.

1189
00:45:57,880 --> 00:45:58,981
Couples?

1190
00:45:59,181 --> 00:46:02,084
Let me review all the options
like any other hawk-eyed bride.

1191
00:46:02,151 --> 00:46:03,553
WILL HE BE HELPFUL, THOUGH?

1192
00:46:03,619 --> 00:46:05,588
I'll make sure they don't push
unnecessary stuff on you.

1193
00:46:06,222 --> 00:46:08,190
- I'm a sucker for sales pitches.
- I'm great at reviewing

1194
00:46:08,257 --> 00:46:09,492
- That matters.
- matters for others.

1195
00:46:09,559 --> 00:46:10,993
- Hey, I love it.
- You do?

1196
00:46:11,060 --> 00:46:12,361
- Sure.
- Great.

1197
00:46:12,662 --> 00:46:15,064
- He's surprisingly family-oriented.
- Tell me about it.

1198
00:46:15,364 --> 00:46:17,533
He has an idealized view of marriage.

1199
00:46:17,600 --> 00:46:18,868
- I see that now.
- Looks that way.

1200
00:46:18,935 --> 00:46:20,870
- He wants a family earnestly.
- He must want it badly.

1201
00:46:21,237 --> 00:46:22,738
Isn't it the same with you guys?

1202
00:46:22,805 --> 00:46:24,340
At this point

1203
00:46:24,407 --> 00:46:26,676
- most of our friends are married.
- So many are married.

1204
00:46:26,742 --> 00:46:28,411
- That's right.
- Many even have kids.

1205
00:46:28,477 --> 00:46:30,212
- Totally.
- As a result

1206
00:46:31,314 --> 00:46:33,416
I can't help but be lonely.

1207
00:46:33,482 --> 00:46:35,084
The friends I used to meet
three times a week

1208
00:46:35,151 --> 00:46:36,552
can only see me once a month.

1209
00:46:36,619 --> 00:46:39,422
When they have kids,
the interval becomes six months.

1210
00:46:39,855 --> 00:46:42,091
Since that's become the norm

1211
00:46:42,158 --> 00:46:44,293
I feel like building my own team

1212
00:46:44,360 --> 00:46:45,861
starting a family of my own

1213
00:46:45,928 --> 00:46:48,598
and having a healthy relationship.

1214
00:46:48,664 --> 00:46:50,800
That might be the ultimate item
on my life's bucket list.

1215
00:46:50,866 --> 00:46:51,867
I never knew.

1216
00:46:52,602 --> 00:46:54,003
My gosh.

1217
00:46:54,070 --> 00:46:58,207
Do you want to get married right away
if you met a suitable partner?

1218
00:46:58,274 --> 00:46:59,275
If that person gives me

1219
00:46:59,342 --> 00:47:02,912
the reassurance that she's the one
I'd like to build my team with

1220
00:47:02,979 --> 00:47:04,113
I'll gladly get married whenever.

1221
00:47:04,880 --> 00:47:05,915
The way he phrased it

1222
00:47:05,982 --> 00:47:07,516
- made me feel like getting married.
- Right?

1223
00:47:07,583 --> 00:47:08,784
It hits different, right?

1224
00:47:08,851 --> 00:47:11,988
The idea of a couple
in love for eternity

1225
00:47:12,054 --> 00:47:13,856
feels like a distant fantasy.

1226
00:47:13,923 --> 00:47:16,626
But the idea of your partner
as your teammate to weather the storm

1227
00:47:16,692 --> 00:47:18,294
and share the joys together

1228
00:47:18,361 --> 00:47:19,562
- definitely hits different.
- Yeah.

1229
00:47:20,329 --> 00:47:22,298
That's the way I feel, too.

1230
00:47:22,365 --> 00:47:25,001
When it comes to ceremonies

1231
00:47:25,067 --> 00:47:27,003
be it an entrance ceremony, a wedding

1232
00:47:27,069 --> 00:47:28,337
or an opening ceremony

1233
00:47:28,404 --> 00:47:31,374
I think you should host all of them.

1234
00:47:32,108 --> 00:47:35,444
I do believe we need those steps.

1235
00:47:35,511 --> 00:47:38,347
All my friends who now have
a happy family have done them.

1236
00:47:38,748 --> 00:47:40,383
I know. Imagine us old.

1237
00:47:40,449 --> 00:47:42,451
Don't you think it'd be better
to have someone with you?

1238
00:47:42,518 --> 00:47:45,087
Without us around, you might spend
your birthday alone again

1239
00:47:45,154 --> 00:47:46,722
- in ten years' time.
- Yeah.

1240
00:47:46,789 --> 00:47:48,824
- With no one to give you a cake.
- Right.

1241
00:47:48,891 --> 00:47:51,293
Will you be searching
for a slow dance partner

1242
00:47:51,360 --> 00:47:52,928
all across the country in ten years?

1243
00:47:52,995 --> 00:47:54,463
LAUGHING

1244
00:47:54,530 --> 00:47:55,898
HE WILL HAVE LIVED ALONE
FOR 30 YEARS THEN

1245
00:47:55,965 --> 00:47:58,701
"WILL ANYONE SLOW DANCE WITH ME
FOR MY 50TH BIRTHDAY?"

1246
00:47:59,001 --> 00:48:00,002
Here's an idea.

1247
00:48:00,069 --> 00:48:02,805
In ten years' time,
if a few of us are still singles

1248
00:48:02,872 --> 00:48:03,873
let's grab a meal

1249
00:48:03,939 --> 00:48:05,374
- and slow dance together.
- In ten years?

1250
00:48:05,441 --> 00:48:06,676
- Yes, in ten years.
- Let's dance.

1251
00:48:06,742 --> 00:48:07,810
QUICKLY TURNING AWAY

1252
00:48:07,877 --> 00:48:09,812
- In ten years?
- Suppose you're alone then.

1253
00:48:10,479 --> 00:48:12,048
Why would you jinx me?

1254
00:48:13,916 --> 00:48:15,651
- I'd be delighted.
- Okay, so that's our deal.

1255
00:48:15,718 --> 00:48:16,919
I'd love that.

1256
00:48:18,120 --> 00:48:19,855
Excuse me.

1257
00:48:19,922 --> 00:48:21,490
Our pianist plays songs on request.

1258
00:48:21,557 --> 00:48:23,793
Is there a song
you'd like in particular?

1259
00:48:24,326 --> 00:48:26,162
THE BIGGEST REASON
BEHIND DANIEL'S RESERVATION

1260
00:48:26,228 --> 00:48:27,229
There we go.

1261
00:48:27,930 --> 00:48:28,931
Do it.

1262
00:48:28,998 --> 00:48:30,399
ON-DEMAND PIANO PERFORMANCE

1263
00:48:30,466 --> 00:48:31,534
Let's do it.

1264
00:48:32,868 --> 00:48:35,471
AVERTING EYE CONTACT

1265
00:48:36,038 --> 00:48:37,139
ALMOST SPEWS OUT FOOD

1266
00:48:37,206 --> 00:48:39,809
THE DANCE PARTNER CANDIDATES
ARE REFUSING TO LOOK AT DANIEL

1267
00:48:39,875 --> 00:48:40,910
Get your plan moving.

1268
00:48:41,844 --> 00:48:42,845
CHECKING THE GIRL PALS

1269
00:48:42,912 --> 00:48:46,449
I would like to ask
for the famous tango song

1270
00:48:46,649 --> 00:48:48,684
- from the movie <i>Scent of a Woman.</i>
- Yes.

1271
00:48:49,051 --> 00:48:50,152
Could we hear that?

1272
00:48:50,219 --> 00:48:52,188
There's no need to be so dramatic
while people are having dinner.

1273
00:48:52,254 --> 00:48:54,423
- I'd like a gentle rendition.
- Of course.

1274
00:48:54,490 --> 00:48:56,392
Would that be possible?

1275
00:48:56,459 --> 00:48:58,194
- Of course.
- Thank you.

1276
00:48:58,260 --> 00:48:59,628
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1277
00:48:59,695 --> 00:49:01,263
Will you be dancing, then?

1278
00:49:01,330 --> 00:49:02,398
AN INTENSE GAZE

1279
00:49:02,465 --> 00:49:04,533
Since the opportunity
presented itself...

1280
00:49:04,600 --> 00:49:05,601
IGNORED

1281
00:49:05,668 --> 00:49:07,336
- I'd like to achieve my dream.
- Go for it.

1282
00:49:07,403 --> 00:49:09,505
- That's what we're here for.
- But then again...

1283
00:49:10,573 --> 00:49:12,508
You might as well do it
when we're all dressed up.

1284
00:49:12,575 --> 00:49:13,576
But...

1285
00:49:13,809 --> 00:49:16,979
- I can't exactly slow dance alone.
- Right.

1286
00:49:17,046 --> 00:49:19,582
- No one slow dances alone.
- Since that's the case...

1287
00:49:19,648 --> 00:49:20,716
But...

1288
00:49:20,783 --> 00:49:23,953
- I can't exactly slow dance alone.
- Right.

1289
00:49:24,019 --> 00:49:26,589
- No one slow dances alone.
- Since that's the case...

1290
00:49:26,655 --> 00:49:28,390
- Excuse me, guys.
- Soo-jin.

1291
00:49:28,457 --> 00:49:29,759
Would it be too much for you?

1292
00:49:29,825 --> 00:49:33,262
WHAT A WAY TO UPSET YOUR STOMACH

1293
00:49:33,496 --> 00:49:35,331
Where are you looking at, Da-hee?

1294
00:49:35,397 --> 00:49:36,565
Is something there?

1295
00:49:37,633 --> 00:49:39,201
Come on, guys.

1296
00:49:39,268 --> 00:49:40,402
STARING AT A FAR AWAY PLACE

1297
00:49:41,203 --> 00:49:43,038
I thought you were done, Do-yeon.

1298
00:49:43,539 --> 00:49:46,075
I tend to eat at a leisurely pace.

1299
00:49:46,142 --> 00:49:47,543
Is that right?

1300
00:49:49,178 --> 00:49:52,448
I'd love to help you guys
achieve your House Squad Goals.

1301
00:49:52,515 --> 00:49:54,683
Da-hee, Do-yeon, and everyone.

1302
00:49:55,017 --> 00:49:58,387
A 40-YEAR-OLD MAN'S SEARCH
FOR A DANCE PARTNER

1303
00:49:59,054 --> 00:50:02,525
AT THAT MOMENT,
THE OWNER RETURNS TO THE PIANO

1304
00:50:02,591 --> 00:50:04,660
AND AN ADDITIONAL GROUP
OF DINERS CAME

1305
00:50:04,727 --> 00:50:06,162
My gosh. So it begins.

1306
00:50:06,762 --> 00:50:07,930
You can say that again.

1307
00:50:08,397 --> 00:50:09,398
There it is.

1308
00:50:09,465 --> 00:50:10,699
HE ISN'T PLAYING THEIR SONG YET

1309
00:50:10,766 --> 00:50:12,735
What do I do?
I feel like my ears are blushing.

1310
00:50:12,802 --> 00:50:13,836
My ears are...

1311
00:50:14,236 --> 00:50:15,938
- Oh, man. My ears...
- What do we do?

1312
00:50:16,005 --> 00:50:17,006
Seeing how you're blushing

1313
00:50:17,072 --> 00:50:19,141
- maybe you don't want it either.
- I honestly...

1314
00:50:19,708 --> 00:50:23,045
IN A VERY GLAMOROUS SETTING

1315
00:50:23,112 --> 00:50:26,482
GRACEFUL MUSIC PLAYS

1316
00:50:26,816 --> 00:50:29,385
ON ONE SIDE OF THE RESTAURANT

1317
00:50:29,451 --> 00:50:32,621
IS A GROUP OF DINERS
FROM ANOTHER COUNTRY

1318
00:50:32,688 --> 00:50:34,690
What do I do?
I feel like my ears are blushing.

1319
00:50:34,757 --> 00:50:36,192
- My gosh.
- My ears are...

1320
00:50:36,258 --> 00:50:37,593
- Oh, man. My ears...
- What do we do?

1321
00:50:37,827 --> 00:50:39,562
Hey, you're turning red, too.

1322
00:50:40,396 --> 00:50:41,397
- He's blushing, too.
- Why?

1323
00:50:41,463 --> 00:50:42,464
What's up with him?

1324
00:50:42,531 --> 00:50:44,200
- Why are you blushing?
- What's going on?

1325
00:50:44,266 --> 00:50:46,001
- Is something the matter?
- He's blushing harder.

1326
00:50:46,068 --> 00:50:47,169
Why are you blushing?

1327
00:50:47,236 --> 00:50:48,971
- What's going on with you?
- What's the matter?

1328
00:50:49,038 --> 00:50:51,106
- Is something the matter?
- Hey, you.

1329
00:50:51,173 --> 00:50:52,174
Why are you blushing?

1330
00:50:52,241 --> 00:50:53,876
RED FLUSH HAS SPREAD DOWN TO HIS NECK

1331
00:50:53,943 --> 00:50:55,244
Even the tips of my ears...

1332
00:50:55,311 --> 00:50:56,412
CLOSE ENOUGH TO SHARE THE NERVES

1333
00:50:56,478 --> 00:50:58,447
- It looks like you're bleeding.
- Guys.

1334
00:50:58,848 --> 00:51:02,952
BUT WITH ONLOOKERS NEARBY

1335
00:51:03,886 --> 00:51:04,954
HE FEELS SO NERVOUS

1336
00:51:05,020 --> 00:51:08,357
THAT HE NEEDS TO DOWN
A GLASS OF WATER

1337
00:51:08,891 --> 00:51:12,728
WATER ISN'T ENOUGH TO SOOTHE HIM

1338
00:51:13,596 --> 00:51:15,564
Can I have a sip of your beer?

1339
00:51:15,631 --> 00:51:17,199
But you don't drink.

1340
00:51:17,266 --> 00:51:19,034
- I'm that confused.
- Are you okay?

1341
00:51:19,101 --> 00:51:20,769
- I'm... I don't know.
- You don't drink.

1342
00:51:20,836 --> 00:51:22,438
My ears are burning hot.

1343
00:51:22,504 --> 00:51:24,340
I don't know what's up with me.

1344
00:51:27,476 --> 00:51:32,548
FINISHES THE REMAINING BEER
WITH AN IRRESISTIBLE POUT

1345
00:51:32,615 --> 00:51:33,782
Hey!

1346
00:51:35,084 --> 00:51:36,452
- Did you finish it?
- Yes, in one go.

1347
00:51:36,518 --> 00:51:38,120
He just gulped down a glass of beer.

1348
00:51:38,520 --> 00:51:40,823
- What?
- He just chugged down beer.

1349
00:51:40,890 --> 00:51:43,492
I don't know what's going on.
All of a sudden, I feel like...

1350
00:51:43,559 --> 00:51:44,994
- I'm a wreck.
- Look at him.

1351
00:51:45,527 --> 00:51:47,162
Gosh, I want to hide under the table.

1352
00:51:47,229 --> 00:51:49,198
- Oh, no.
- Please spare me.

1353
00:51:49,265 --> 00:51:50,399
SECONDHAND EMBARRASSMENT HITS HARD

1354
00:51:50,466 --> 00:51:52,468
SCANNING

1355
00:51:52,534 --> 00:51:53,602
Are you done?

1356
00:51:53,903 --> 00:51:54,970
I'm still drinking it.

1357
00:51:55,371 --> 00:51:56,538
Can I take a sip?

1358
00:51:56,605 --> 00:51:57,640
For real?

1359
00:51:57,706 --> 00:51:58,707
Yeah, I really need it.

1360
00:52:00,042 --> 00:52:01,210
He's drinking again!

1361
00:52:01,277 --> 00:52:02,878
- What's going on?
- What's up with you?

1362
00:52:03,846 --> 00:52:05,981
I think he's trying to find courage
with the help of alcohol.

1363
00:52:06,248 --> 00:52:08,384
It's just that... Let's be real.

1364
00:52:08,450 --> 00:52:10,586
- This is my only shot at my dream.
- Sure.

1365
00:52:10,653 --> 00:52:14,023
- Just enjoy it.
- My legs are shaking, though.

1366
00:52:14,089 --> 00:52:16,492
STILL NERVOUS

1367
00:52:18,160 --> 00:52:20,396
I think we're all relaxed now.

1368
00:52:22,197 --> 00:52:24,199
- There it is.
- Hey, this is your song.

1369
00:52:24,800 --> 00:52:28,904
DANIEL REQUESTED <i>POR UNA CABEZA</i>
FROM <i>SCENT OF A WOMAN</i>

1370
00:52:29,538 --> 00:52:34,510
IT'S TIME TO ENTER THE SCENE
YOUNG DANIEL ONCE DREAMED OF

1371
00:52:36,011 --> 00:52:38,213
- It's up to Daniel.
- Who will he choose?

1372
00:52:38,280 --> 00:52:39,882
Who will he choose?

1373
00:52:39,949 --> 00:52:43,152
To which lady will he ask,
"Shall we dance?"

1374
00:52:43,218 --> 00:52:44,219
Do-yeon.

1375
00:52:46,088 --> 00:52:48,891
A SUDDEN ATTACK OF FOOD COMA

1376
00:52:50,426 --> 00:52:51,427
Are you sleeping?

1377
00:52:52,328 --> 00:52:53,662
- Da-hee.
- Here we go.

1378
00:52:53,729 --> 00:52:55,831
NEVER MEET HIS EYES

1379
00:52:55,898 --> 00:52:57,099
Da-hee.

1380
00:52:57,599 --> 00:52:59,268
LONGINGLY

1381
00:52:59,335 --> 00:53:00,336
Soo-jin.

1382
00:53:01,337 --> 00:53:03,072
Why are my lips so chapped?

1383
00:53:03,138 --> 00:53:04,139
AVOIDING THE SUBJECT

1384
00:53:04,506 --> 00:53:05,774
You have to hit the stage now.

1385
00:53:05,841 --> 00:53:07,142
Come on, it's his House Squad Goal.

1386
00:53:07,209 --> 00:53:08,510
Help him.

1387
00:53:09,178 --> 00:53:10,245
- Yeah.
- Help him.

1388
00:53:11,180 --> 00:53:12,514
Hey, he got up.

1389
00:53:12,581 --> 00:53:13,649
He's on the move.

1390
00:53:13,716 --> 00:53:15,484
HE'S GOING TO HIS PARTNER

1391
00:53:16,752 --> 00:53:19,888
WHOSE HAND WILL HE ASK TO HOLD?

1392
00:53:20,122 --> 00:53:21,957
THE LADY HE APPROACHES

1393
00:53:22,024 --> 00:53:25,127
WILL HELP DANIEL
REALIZE HIS OLD DREAM

1394
00:53:25,361 --> 00:53:28,263
HE'S ON HIS WAY TO HER

1395
00:53:32,868 --> 00:53:33,869
Soo-jin.

1396
00:53:33,936 --> 00:53:36,205
THE NAME HE CALLS OUT IS SOO-JIN

1397
00:53:36,271 --> 00:53:37,339
Soo-jin.

1398
00:53:37,406 --> 00:53:39,608
RED SOO-JIN GETS THE ROLE
FOR WEARING THE RED DRESS

1399
00:53:39,675 --> 00:53:40,876
Great!

1400
00:53:41,677 --> 00:53:43,078
Great!

1401
00:53:45,581 --> 00:53:48,150
SMILING BROADLY OUT OF RELIEF

1402
00:53:48,450 --> 00:53:50,619
Will you dance with me?

1403
00:53:52,888 --> 00:53:54,023
SHE TAKES HIS HAND

1404
00:53:54,456 --> 00:53:55,457
Okay.

1405
00:53:55,524 --> 00:53:57,760
LIKE THE BOLD COLOR OF HER DRESS,
SHE ACCEPTS FEARLESSLY

1406
00:53:59,795 --> 00:54:01,163
We're here anyway. Let's do this.

1407
00:54:02,297 --> 00:54:03,298
They look good together.

1408
00:54:03,365 --> 00:54:05,034
STANDING TALL

1409
00:54:05,701 --> 00:54:06,802
EVERYONE SNAPS TO ATTENTION

1410
00:54:06,869 --> 00:54:08,504
We're here anyway. Let's do this.

1411
00:54:09,571 --> 00:54:11,940
AMAZED

1412
00:54:12,007 --> 00:54:13,475
Other diners look startled.

1413
00:54:13,542 --> 00:54:14,943
Yeah.

1414
00:54:15,344 --> 00:54:17,212
THEY HEAD TO TONIGHT'S STAGE

1415
00:54:17,279 --> 00:54:18,280
Is this our stage?

1416
00:54:18,847 --> 00:54:20,382
I'm not sure.

1417
00:54:20,582 --> 00:54:22,084
- It's just the two of them now.
- Of course.

1418
00:54:22,151 --> 00:54:23,419
And so it begins.

1419
00:54:24,620 --> 00:54:25,988
- It's hot in here.
- I'm shaking.

1420
00:54:26,055 --> 00:54:27,089
Look, Daniel.

1421
00:54:27,156 --> 00:54:28,991
Think as if we're on a drama set.

1422
00:54:29,058 --> 00:54:30,592
Everyone else is
an extra on the show.

1423
00:54:30,659 --> 00:54:31,660
We're the main characters.

1424
00:54:31,727 --> 00:54:32,828
So we're on a set?

1425
00:54:32,895 --> 00:54:34,096
- You bet.
- Got it.

1426
00:54:34,463 --> 00:54:35,664
Doesn't that give you courage?

1427
00:54:35,731 --> 00:54:37,766
SOO-JIN OFFERS WORDS OF ENCOURAGEMENT
TO NERVOUS DANIEL

1428
00:54:39,101 --> 00:54:40,102
SO CLOSE

1429
00:54:40,169 --> 00:54:41,170
This is it.

1430
00:54:41,537 --> 00:54:42,905
MY GOSH!

1431
00:54:43,705 --> 00:54:45,407
IS SHE PRETENDING NOT TO SEE IT?

1432
00:54:45,808 --> 00:54:47,643
THE DANCE BEGINS
WITH SOO-JIN LEADING THE PAIR

1433
00:54:47,709 --> 00:54:48,911
- Left.
- Okay.

1434
00:54:49,578 --> 00:54:50,846
There we go.

1435
00:54:50,913 --> 00:54:52,948
EXTREMELY NERVOUS

1436
00:54:53,015 --> 00:54:54,216
- Now, to the right.
- Okay.

1437
00:54:55,417 --> 00:54:56,585
FOCUSING ON EACH OTHER

1438
00:54:56,652 --> 00:54:57,886
- Now, to the right.
- Okay.

1439
00:54:57,953 --> 00:54:59,855
THEY LEARN TO MOVE IN HARMONY

1440
00:54:59,922 --> 00:55:01,156
- To the left.
- Again to the left.

1441
00:55:02,091 --> 00:55:03,392
Hold on.

1442
00:55:03,559 --> 00:55:05,727
Let's move one step to the right.

1443
00:55:05,794 --> 00:55:06,929
- Okay.
- Let's try that move.

1444
00:55:06,995 --> 00:55:07,996
Stretching out.

1445
00:55:10,399 --> 00:55:13,435
THE NEWFOUND CONFIDENCE
IS HELPING HIM CARRY OUT HIS DREAM

1446
00:55:14,837 --> 00:55:16,371
Good. He's done it anyhow.

1447
00:55:16,438 --> 00:55:17,439
A RATHER STRANGE WATCH PARTY

1448
00:55:17,506 --> 00:55:19,208
Hey, they look so lovely together.

1449
00:55:19,842 --> 00:55:20,843
Just a second.

1450
00:55:20,909 --> 00:55:22,077
EVEN THE AUDIENCE SEEMS SATISFIED

1451
00:55:22,578 --> 00:55:23,579
You two look great together.

1452
00:55:23,645 --> 00:55:25,214
- I know.
- Don't they look good together?

1453
00:55:25,280 --> 00:55:26,615
They make a cute couple.

1454
00:55:27,249 --> 00:55:28,250
One step this way.

1455
00:55:28,317 --> 00:55:29,318
THEY LOOK MORE NATURAL NOW

1456
00:55:31,620 --> 00:55:32,988
Hey, they found their rhythm.

1457
00:55:33,055 --> 00:55:34,289
AFTER PRACTICING THE STEPS TOGETHER

1458
00:55:34,690 --> 00:55:36,892
HERE COMES THE HIGHLIGHT

1459
00:55:38,594 --> 00:55:39,895
One step, and then we'll spread out.

1460
00:55:42,030 --> 00:55:43,665
RIGHT INTO HIS ARMS

1461
00:55:46,702 --> 00:55:49,471
DANIEL'S DREAM CAME TRUE PERFECTLY

1462
00:55:51,907 --> 00:55:53,041
Great!

1463
00:55:53,909 --> 00:55:54,910
STOPS MIDWAY

1464
00:55:55,310 --> 00:55:56,311
Great!

1465
00:55:56,378 --> 00:55:57,513
One more time.

1466
00:55:58,714 --> 00:56:01,416
HE USED TO SPEND HIS BIRTHDAYS ALONE

1467
00:56:02,050 --> 00:56:03,185
BUT TODAY

1468
00:56:03,252 --> 00:56:04,319
I don't know.

1469
00:56:04,386 --> 00:56:07,890
HE HAS A FRIEND WHO'S READY
TO HELP HIM REALIZE HIS DREAM

1470
00:56:08,757 --> 00:56:10,092
It's too hot, Daniel. What do I do?

1471
00:56:10,159 --> 00:56:11,193
I'm dying here.

1472
00:56:11,260 --> 00:56:13,195
THE MUSIC COMES TO A TIMELY END

1473
00:56:13,262 --> 00:56:14,930
OR NOT

1474
00:56:14,997 --> 00:56:16,064
- It's just...
- One last thing.

1475
00:56:17,032 --> 00:56:18,267
Again?

1476
00:56:18,767 --> 00:56:21,069
THEN, LET'S SPIN

1477
00:56:22,271 --> 00:56:26,208
EVERYONE BURSTS INTO LAUGHTER

1478
00:56:26,275 --> 00:56:27,376
Turn... Oh, that way?

1479
00:56:27,442 --> 00:56:29,711
Turn. Go ahead.

1480
00:56:30,379 --> 00:56:31,480
Oh, dear.

1481
00:56:31,547 --> 00:56:33,348
THANKS TO THE PASSIONATE OWNER

1482
00:56:33,949 --> 00:56:35,284
SOO-JIN TURNED

1483
00:56:35,350 --> 00:56:37,519
TURNED AGAIN

1484
00:56:37,586 --> 00:56:39,888
UNTIL SHE LOST HER MIND

1485
