1730
01:06:22,665 --> 01:06:24,700
GETTING CHANGED

1731
01:06:24,767 --> 01:06:25,834
I'm coming upstairs!

1732
01:06:25,901 --> 01:06:26,902
- Okay.
- All right.

1733
01:06:26,969 --> 01:06:27,970
STARTLED

1734
01:06:28,037 --> 01:06:29,838
- Why is she coming up, though?
- What's up, Da-hee?

1735
01:06:30,039 --> 01:06:31,340
I'm coming upstairs!

1736
01:06:31,407 --> 01:06:32,708
NO HESITATION IN HER STEPS

1737
01:06:32,775 --> 01:06:34,209
THEY GOT USED TO THE HOUSE SHARE

1738
01:06:34,276 --> 01:06:35,277
This.

1739
01:06:35,344 --> 01:06:36,478
- What's up, Da-hee?
- This.

1740
01:06:36,545 --> 01:06:37,780
- Just a second.
- Whose is it?

1741
01:06:38,614 --> 01:06:40,149
IN A HURRY

1742
01:06:41,417 --> 01:06:43,352
This. Whose is it?

1743
01:06:44,286 --> 01:06:45,721
SIGHS

1744
01:06:47,556 --> 01:06:49,058
Let me just wash my feet.

1745
01:06:49,558 --> 01:06:51,860
- You said you wouldn't wash up.
- I need to wash my feet.

1746
01:06:51,927 --> 01:06:52,928
Jeez, you punk.

1747
01:06:52,995 --> 01:06:55,197
- What? Are feet no exception?
- Jeez.

1748
01:06:55,397 --> 01:06:56,632
Just my feet, okay?

1749
01:06:56,699 --> 01:06:59,234
Did you know I showered
while Keun-suk was in the bathroom?

1750
01:06:59,301 --> 01:07:00,302
CHORTLES

1751
01:07:00,369 --> 01:07:02,938
Keun-suk was washing his face

1752
01:07:03,005 --> 01:07:04,173
and I took a shower in the back.

1753
01:07:04,239 --> 01:07:05,741
THEY'RE CLOSER THAN A REAL FAMILY

1754
01:07:06,442 --> 01:07:07,443
LET'S CHECK ON SOO-JIN

1755
01:07:07,509 --> 01:07:09,278
DANIEL'S DANCE PARTNER
WHO DID THE HEAVY LIFTING

1756
01:07:11,246 --> 01:07:13,182
DIVING INTO THE BED, TOO

1757
01:07:13,248 --> 01:07:14,283
My back.

1758
01:07:14,349 --> 01:07:17,119
AND SHE FELL ASLEEP RIGHT AWAY

1759
01:07:17,186 --> 01:07:20,022
OR MAYBE NOT

1760
01:07:21,523 --> 01:07:24,526
A SUDDEN FIT CHECK
IN THE MIDDLE OF THE NIGHT

1761
01:07:24,593 --> 01:07:26,295
STARING

1762
01:07:26,729 --> 01:07:28,464
NODDING

1763
01:07:28,530 --> 01:07:30,899
NOT BAD

1764
01:07:35,003 --> 01:07:38,874
LET'S GET WASHED UP NOW

1765
01:07:43,779 --> 01:07:46,782
HAVING TROUBLE WITH THE ZIPPER

1766
01:07:47,683 --> 01:07:49,284
I need to go ask a favor.

1767
01:07:50,119 --> 01:07:52,221
You know how it is, right?
The issue with the back zipper.

1768
01:07:52,287 --> 01:07:54,456
- Go inside.
- Yes, right in here.

1769
01:07:54,523 --> 01:07:55,524
DA-HEE IS CALLED

1770
01:07:56,625 --> 01:07:57,726
- Thanks, Da-hee.
- All good?

1771
01:07:57,793 --> 01:07:59,128
Thank you.

1772
01:07:59,194 --> 01:08:00,529
- Get changed.
- Sure.

1773
01:08:01,263 --> 01:08:02,898
SCANNING THE ROOM

1774
01:08:02,965 --> 01:08:04,500
Your room's clean today.

1775
01:08:04,566 --> 01:08:06,235
FOR A CHANGE!

1776
01:08:08,570 --> 01:08:11,573
SHE'S FOUND THE POLAROID SHOTS
THEY TOOK EARLIER

1777
01:08:12,207 --> 01:08:14,510
PLEASED

1778
01:08:16,745 --> 01:08:20,282
PUTTING UP THE TOKENS
OF THE DAY'S MEMORY

1779
01:08:22,918 --> 01:08:24,453
ALL SMILES

1780
01:08:25,921 --> 01:08:28,423
FROM THE FIRST DAY UP TO TODAY

1781
01:08:28,490 --> 01:08:33,228
THE BOARD IS NOW FILLED
WITH MEMENTOS OF THEIR TIME TOGETHER

1782
01:08:33,862 --> 01:08:41,236
A NEW DAWN
AFTER DANIEL'S BUSTLING BIRTHDAY

1783
01:08:42,304 --> 01:08:45,941
IT IS UNUSUALLY QUIET TODAY

1784
01:08:46,441 --> 01:08:50,646
FATIGUED BY ALL THE DANCING,
THE GIRLS ARE DEEP IN SLEEP

1785
01:08:51,313 --> 01:08:53,282
SNORING

1786
01:08:53,348 --> 01:08:56,785
THE GUYS HAD
AN ESPECIALLY EVENTFUL DAY

1787
01:08:57,085 --> 01:08:58,086
MUMBLING

1788
01:08:59,121 --> 01:09:01,290
OUT OF THEM ALL

1789
01:09:01,356 --> 01:09:03,692
THE FULL DAY WOULD'VE WORN OUT
THIS GUY THE MOST

1790
01:09:03,759 --> 01:09:05,861
HIS BIRTHDAY, THE POTTERY DATE,
AND THE SLOW DANCING

1791
01:09:06,528 --> 01:09:08,163
OH, MAN

1792
01:09:08,964 --> 01:09:09,965
GROANS

1793
01:09:10,232 --> 01:09:13,902
NOW 40 YEARS AND 1 DAY OLD,
DANIEL WAKES UP WITH A GROAN

1794
01:09:15,270 --> 01:09:18,674
SEVERE BED HAIR

1795
01:09:18,740 --> 01:09:21,777
DROOL TRACK
LET ME WIPE THAT

1796
01:09:22,578 --> 01:09:25,547
HIS MORNING FACE SOMEHOW GOT WORSE
AFTER HIS BIRTHDAY

1797
01:09:31,386 --> 01:09:36,391
IS THE FATIGUE WAY WORSE
NOW THAT HE LEFT HIS 30S BEHIND?

1798
01:09:36,692 --> 01:09:39,361
GROANING

1799
01:09:41,096 --> 01:09:43,765
FINALLY GETTING UP
AFTER COAXING HIS TIRED BODY

1800
01:09:45,200 --> 01:09:46,401
SIGHS

1801
01:09:48,437 --> 01:09:51,240
VISITING THE KITCHEN
TO GET SOME WATER

1802
01:09:51,306 --> 01:09:54,610
STAGGERING

1803
01:09:55,444 --> 01:09:57,613
ENGINE REVVING

1804
01:09:57,679 --> 01:09:59,047
A LITTLE YELP

1805
01:09:59,548 --> 01:10:03,118
IT'S NOT EASY TO STRETCH YOURSELF
WHEN YOU'RE 40 YEARS AND 1 DAY OLD

1806
01:10:03,518 --> 01:10:05,487
I'm exhausted.

1807
01:10:05,554 --> 01:10:08,190
HAVE THE ENERGY OF A NEWBORN

1808
01:10:08,257 --> 01:10:11,560
COMPLETELY DRAINED

1809
01:10:13,996 --> 01:10:14,997
FINALLY STARTS MOVING AGAIN

1810
01:10:15,063 --> 01:10:16,732
I'm exhausted.

1811
01:10:24,306 --> 01:10:26,074
SUDDENLY REMINDED

1812
01:10:26,141 --> 01:10:29,912
OF THE GLORIOUS MORNING YESTERDAY

1813
01:10:30,512 --> 01:10:33,248
THE KITCHEN BUSTLED WITH PEOPLE

1814
01:10:33,982 --> 01:10:36,051
SCRATCHING HIMSELF

1815
01:10:36,118 --> 01:10:39,521
THIS LONELY MORNING
DEFINITELY PALES IN COMPARISON

1816
01:10:41,189 --> 01:10:42,190
SCRATCHING SOME MORE

1817
01:10:42,257 --> 01:10:45,727
MORNING GROOMING OF THE 40-YEAR-OLD
ALLERGIC TO LONELINESS

1818
01:10:46,929 --> 01:10:51,099
WHAT WILL HE HAVE FOR BREAKFAST
AS A 40-YEAR-AND-1-DAY-OLD?

1819
01:10:52,367 --> 01:10:55,070
A SUPER SIMPLE BOWL OF CEREAL

1820
01:10:55,137 --> 01:10:57,606
WITH AN EXTRA LARGE PORTION

1821
01:11:00,042 --> 01:11:03,145
A BIG BITE
AFTER MIXING THEM HALFHEARTEDLY

1822
01:11:03,478 --> 01:11:06,081
SPECIAL TREATMENT IS OVER
IT'S TIME FOR LONELY BREAKFAST

1823
01:11:06,148 --> 01:11:08,383
NODDING FOR SOME REASON

1824
01:11:10,485 --> 01:11:12,487
SLURP

1825
01:11:12,888 --> 01:11:15,490
HE LOOKS RATHER PITIFUL

1826
01:11:16,758 --> 01:11:18,694
SCRATCHING

1827
01:11:18,760 --> 01:11:19,928
Is everyone asleep?

1828
01:11:21,463 --> 01:11:24,132
How can everyone still be in bed?

1829
01:11:24,199 --> 01:11:25,334
THE FAM CAME TO HIS MIND

1830
01:11:25,400 --> 01:11:29,638
WHILE EVERYONE IS UP
AND GETTING READY FOR ANOTHER DAY

1831
01:11:30,138 --> 01:11:31,974
ONE PERSON IS DEEP IN SLEEP YET AGAIN

1832
01:11:32,040 --> 01:11:34,443
IT IS SOO-JIN, MS. INSOMNIAC

1833
01:11:36,345 --> 01:11:37,779
SOO-JIN IS NO LONGER INSOMNIAC

1834
01:11:37,846 --> 01:11:39,281
CONFIRMED

1835
01:11:40,349 --> 01:11:42,117
MAYBE THEY'RE HERE?

1836
01:11:42,184 --> 01:11:44,386
HE CAME ALL THE WAY TO THE BASEMENT
TO FIND THE OTHERS

1837
01:11:45,087 --> 01:11:46,088
EMPTY

1838
01:11:48,357 --> 01:11:49,725
Did they go somewhere without me?

1839
01:11:49,791 --> 01:11:50,792
LONESOME

1840
01:11:51,693 --> 01:11:55,430
DANIEL IS FEELING
ESPECIALLY LONELY TODAY

1841
01:11:55,497 --> 01:11:56,932
Are they still in bed?

1842
01:11:58,000 --> 01:12:01,636
HE CHOOSES TO ESCAPE
THE LONELINESS THROUGH MUSIC

1843
01:12:01,703 --> 01:12:03,905
SOULFUL

1844
01:12:05,440 --> 01:12:11,413
THE SONG SOUNDS
EVEN MORE SENTIMENTAL TODAY

1845
01:12:11,847 --> 01:12:15,584
9 A.M.
A BREAK-UP SONG WITHOUT WARM-UP

1846
01:12:20,355 --> 01:12:24,993
SAYING GOODBYE TO HIS 30S

1847
01:12:26,028 --> 01:12:31,066
STARTING THE FIRST DAY IN HIS 40S
BRIGHT AND EARLY WITH A BREAK-UP SONG

1848
01:12:32,567 --> 01:12:33,668
I don't even know anymore.

1849
01:12:36,238 --> 01:12:37,272
EVERYTHING FEELS HEAVIER NOW

1850
01:12:37,339 --> 01:12:38,473
It's too hot.

1851
01:12:39,741 --> 01:12:40,876
YOU'RE UP, JAE-HYEON

1852
01:12:40,942 --> 01:12:42,544
GOOD MORNING

1853
01:12:42,811 --> 01:12:44,079
Shall we get going?

1854
01:12:44,146 --> 01:12:45,547
- We should.
- Let's go.

1855
01:12:45,614 --> 01:12:46,748
- Let's go.
- Okay.

1856
01:12:46,815 --> 01:12:48,850
Off we go.

1857
01:12:48,917 --> 01:12:50,752
- Please hop into the van.
- Who's driving?

1858
01:12:50,819 --> 01:12:52,287
I know the address, so I'll drive.

1859
01:12:52,354 --> 01:12:54,122
- I made the reservation.
- All right, then.

1860
01:12:54,523 --> 01:12:56,725
I just realized this is
Jae-hyeon's first House Squad Goal.

1861
01:12:56,792 --> 01:12:59,094
It's actually more exciting
when it's your House Squad Goal.

1862
01:12:59,161 --> 01:13:00,395
Look at me, all talkative.

1863
01:13:00,762 --> 01:13:02,364
IS TODAY JAE-HYEON'S DAY?

1864
01:13:02,664 --> 01:13:04,032
YESTERDAY EVENING

1865
01:13:04,099 --> 01:13:06,334
I only had a few ideas
for the House Squad Goal early on.

1866
01:13:06,401 --> 01:13:07,536
- Yeah.
- Well...

1867
01:13:07,602 --> 01:13:09,304
- You barely had any.
- A random idea hit me.

1868
01:13:09,371 --> 01:13:12,307
I'd love to get a family portrait.

1869
01:13:12,374 --> 01:13:13,542
We'll visit a studio...

1870
01:13:13,608 --> 01:13:15,077
Like the ones back in our childhood

1871
01:13:15,143 --> 01:13:16,778
- about this size?
- Like the ones in studios.

1872
01:13:16,845 --> 01:13:21,783
I know it's nothing major,
but I wasn't able to get it done.

1873
01:13:21,850 --> 01:13:23,752
- You do need a family first.
- Yeah.

1874
01:13:23,819 --> 01:13:25,420
- Exactly.
- I wasn't able to get it done.

1875
01:13:25,487 --> 01:13:27,122
AI can generate photos nowadays.

1876
01:13:27,189 --> 01:13:28,190
- That doesn't count.
- Really?

1877
01:13:28,256 --> 01:13:30,859
- Those are fake.
- They lack human warmth.

1878
01:13:30,926 --> 01:13:32,494
Why would you even say that?

1879
01:13:32,561 --> 01:13:34,896
You're so unromantic.

1880
01:13:35,864 --> 01:13:37,933
Are you showing your true colors
because you got your dance?

1881
01:13:39,835 --> 01:13:42,170
GETTING AN EARFUL
RIGHT FROM THE MORNING

1882
01:13:42,237 --> 01:13:44,206
- Your birthday is over, Daniel.
- Oh, man.

1883
01:13:44,272 --> 01:13:46,408
- I can't even make a joke now.
- Do-yeon rules.

1884
01:13:46,475 --> 01:13:48,477
So yesterday was a special day.

1885
01:13:49,277 --> 01:13:51,947
- Your birthday is over.
- You turned on me so quickly.

1886
01:13:52,013 --> 01:13:53,348
IT'S A MATTER OF HIS SURVIVAL NOW

1887
01:13:53,915 --> 01:13:55,951
- It feels so strange.
- It does.

1888
01:13:56,017 --> 01:13:57,819
My family has never had
a family portrait taken.

1889
01:13:57,886 --> 01:13:59,421
- Mine hasn't either.
- All we have

1890
01:13:59,754 --> 01:14:00,989
are photos taken outside.

1891
01:14:01,456 --> 01:14:04,192
- Like on a graduation day and so on.
- I get it.

1892
01:14:04,259 --> 01:14:05,994
We only took group photos
when there was an event.

1893
01:14:06,061 --> 01:14:08,130
- Yeah, and you're an only child.
- I'm an only child

1894
01:14:08,196 --> 01:14:12,400
and I don't think I've asked
my parents for a group photo.

1895
01:14:12,634 --> 01:14:13,702
You don't really get to

1896
01:14:13,768 --> 01:14:15,137
- visit studios together.
- No.

1897
01:14:16,705 --> 01:14:18,006
<i>- We're here, everyone.</i>
<i>- Okay.</i>

1898
01:14:18,073 --> 01:14:19,875
<i>- Thanks, man.</i>
<i>- Thank you, Jae-hyeon.</i>

1899
01:14:19,941 --> 01:14:21,543
<i>- All right.</i>
<i>- Well done!</i>

1900
01:14:23,545 --> 01:14:24,546
My gosh.

1901
01:14:24,613 --> 01:14:26,047
- A photo studio.
- It's right there!

1902
01:14:26,114 --> 01:14:27,716
IT'S BEEN SO LONG
SINCE THEY VISITED ONE

1903
01:14:27,782 --> 01:14:28,783
After you.

1904
01:14:28,850 --> 01:14:29,851
LOCAL STUDIOS ARE NOW RARE

1905
01:14:29,918 --> 01:14:30,919
Welcome.

1906
01:14:30,986 --> 01:14:32,487
Hello.

1907
01:14:32,554 --> 01:14:33,855
Hello.

1908
01:14:33,922 --> 01:14:36,258
- I have a reservation.
- At 1 p.m., correct?

1909
01:14:36,324 --> 01:14:37,926
Okay, let's go downstairs.

1910
01:14:38,493 --> 01:14:41,129
A RARE VISIT TO THE PHOTO STUDIO
FOR A FAMILY PICTURE

1911
01:14:41,630 --> 01:14:44,199
- What on earth?
- It's so spacious here.

1912
01:14:44,866 --> 01:14:46,635
STARTLED

1913
01:14:46,701 --> 01:14:48,303
The place is huge.

1914
01:14:48,370 --> 01:14:50,872
This really feels old-school.

1915
01:14:53,375 --> 01:14:55,143
<i>It takes you back, doesn't it?</i>

1916
01:14:55,544 --> 01:14:59,447
BACK IN THE DAY, EVERY FAMILY
HAD A FAMILY PORTRAIT AT HOME

1917
01:15:00,115 --> 01:15:03,752
FAMILY GROUPS
DON'T VISIT AS OFTEN NOW

1918
01:15:04,719 --> 01:15:08,957
BUT HE HAS BEEN CAPTURING WARM BOND
BETWEEN PEOPLE FOR 40 YEARS

1919
01:15:09,624 --> 01:15:10,759
- Jae-hyeon.
- Yes?

1920
01:15:10,825 --> 01:15:12,360
How big do you want the photo to be?

1921
01:15:12,427 --> 01:15:14,796
Would this be enough,
or do you want to go larger?

1922
01:15:14,863 --> 01:15:16,431
It'll be overwhelming
if we make it too large.

1923
01:15:16,498 --> 01:15:17,832
Yes, will that do?

1924
01:15:17,899 --> 01:15:19,467
- So this one?
- How's that?

1925
01:15:19,534 --> 01:15:20,969
WHICH PHOTO ARE THEY TALKING ABOUT?

1926
01:15:21,036 --> 01:15:22,404
Where are we hanging it anyway?

1927
01:15:22,470 --> 01:15:24,506
- Above the couch.
- On the wall behind the couch.

1928
01:15:24,573 --> 01:15:25,774
Oh, there?

1929
01:15:25,840 --> 01:15:26,841
THE MOST EYE-CATCHING SPOT

1930
01:15:26,908 --> 01:15:28,410
<i>- A huge painting's there, right?</i>
<i>- Yeah.</i>

1931
01:15:29,578 --> 01:15:31,680
A BACKGROUND SCREEN ROLLS DOWN
AS THEY DISCUSS THE SIZE

1932
01:15:31,746 --> 01:15:33,048
Hey, the screen is coming down.

1933
01:15:33,782 --> 01:15:34,816
It's a state-of-the-art system.

1934
01:15:35,850 --> 01:15:37,485
It's coming down.

1935
01:15:37,552 --> 01:15:39,054
- This is it.
- So this is how it works.

1936
01:15:39,120 --> 01:15:41,790
- You need a little touch like this.
- I get it now.

1937
01:15:42,357 --> 01:15:44,259
- A bit like an aura.
- Exactly.

1938
01:15:44,859 --> 01:15:45,994
Hey, I like this.

1939
01:15:46,061 --> 01:15:48,129
- I'd like this one. It looks warm.
- Really?

1940
01:15:48,196 --> 01:15:49,698
- Get in there, Soo-jin.
- Good idea.

1941
01:15:49,764 --> 01:15:51,099
- Me?
- Let me see how it looks.

1942
01:15:51,166 --> 01:15:52,400
Get in the center.

1943
01:15:53,535 --> 01:15:54,536
Like this.

1944
01:15:54,603 --> 01:15:55,670
DRESS CODE IS WHITE TOP AND JEANS

1945
01:15:55,737 --> 01:15:58,039
- Does my white top look okay?
- Yeah, it does.

1946
01:15:58,106 --> 01:15:59,541
Hey, this looks great.

1947
01:15:59,608 --> 01:16:00,875
- So pretty.
- I like it.

1948
01:16:01,810 --> 01:16:03,411
I don't think this is it.

1949
01:16:03,845 --> 01:16:06,181
- Is it too textbook?
- It's not quite what I want.

1950
01:16:07,148 --> 01:16:09,150
- It looks a bit blotched.
- I see.

1951
01:16:09,217 --> 01:16:10,352
METICULOUS ABOUT HIS DREAM PROJECT

1952
01:16:10,418 --> 01:16:12,254
You look perfect, Soo-jin.

1953
01:16:12,320 --> 01:16:13,755
DISSATISFIED BUT UNABLE TO SPEAK UP

1954
01:16:13,822 --> 01:16:15,624
The screen looks pretty decent to me.

1955
01:16:16,124 --> 01:16:18,260
- That's one option.
- Okay.

1956
01:16:18,326 --> 01:16:19,628
I'll show you the second one.

1957
01:16:21,096 --> 01:16:23,031
RELIEVED

1958
01:16:24,032 --> 01:16:25,166
THIS IS EXCITING

1959
01:16:25,233 --> 01:16:27,002
- This one has curtains.
- There it is.

1960
01:16:27,402 --> 01:16:28,703
IT'S RIGHT UP MY ALLEY

1961
01:16:28,770 --> 01:16:29,871
I've never seen this before.

1962
01:16:30,338 --> 01:16:32,007
Let's go with this.

1963
01:16:32,474 --> 01:16:34,509
- It's giving European royal family.
- Yeah.

1964
01:16:34,576 --> 01:16:36,511
Can't we go for a classical vibe
with this one?

1965
01:16:36,845 --> 01:16:37,912
Let's use this.

1966
01:16:38,580 --> 01:16:40,515
- Isn't it beautiful?
- It's giving the Middle Ages.

1967
01:16:40,582 --> 01:16:41,750
Yes, exactly.

1968
01:16:42,250 --> 01:16:44,119
THE MIDDLE AGES?

1969
01:16:44,953 --> 01:16:47,222
KNIGHT KYUNG!

1970
01:16:47,289 --> 01:16:48,723
- You look like a princess.
- You do.

1971
01:16:48,790 --> 01:16:50,992
- I don't think so.
- But you do look like one.

1972
01:16:51,293 --> 01:16:53,395
LOOKS LIKE SHE PREFERS KNIGHT

1973
01:16:53,628 --> 01:16:56,164
- It has a romantic charm.
- Tell me about it.

1974
01:16:56,231 --> 01:16:57,465
A RARE QUALITY IN THE AI AGE

1975
01:16:57,532 --> 01:16:58,867
It must've been popular for a reason.

1976
01:16:58,933 --> 01:17:01,636
- I've never had a family portrait.
- Me neither.

1977
01:17:01,703 --> 01:17:03,772
- Have any of you had one?
- No.

1978
01:17:03,838 --> 01:17:06,207
I never had a photo
of my first birthday.

1979
01:17:06,941 --> 01:17:09,010
Do you want a photo...

1980
01:17:09,077 --> 01:17:10,078
A photo in that style?

1981
01:17:10,145 --> 01:17:11,846
Should we have a <i>doljabi </i>ceremony?

1982
01:17:12,514 --> 01:17:13,948
Should we give him the experience?

1983
01:17:14,015 --> 01:17:15,016
Do I get to pick an item?

1984
01:17:15,517 --> 01:17:17,252
ALMOST FORTY
FIRST BIRTHDAY

1985
01:17:17,319 --> 01:17:18,420
Just a second.

1986
01:17:18,486 --> 01:17:20,188
- He's cute. Let's snap one for him.
- Okay.

1987
01:17:20,255 --> 01:17:22,424
- Let's take a shot for him.
- Yeah, let's do that.

1988
01:17:22,490 --> 01:17:24,559
The others' first birthday photos
made me so jealous.

1989
01:17:24,626 --> 01:17:25,627
You're getting yours now.

1990
01:17:25,694 --> 01:17:28,029
Hey, that's good.
That camera will get us a great pic.

1991
01:17:28,763 --> 01:17:29,864
HE'S REALLY HAPPY ABOUT THIS

1992
01:17:29,931 --> 01:17:30,932
"First birthday."

1993
01:17:30,999 --> 01:17:32,767
- I got it.
- Hey, you look really good.

1994
01:17:34,102 --> 01:17:36,538
- I love it.
- That's a cute one.

1995
01:17:36,604 --> 01:17:37,839
<i>Wow, you did a great job.</i>

1996
01:17:37,906 --> 01:17:39,674
<i>- Well done.</i>
<i>- The backdrop looks nice.</i>

1997
01:17:39,741 --> 01:17:42,844
- Have a seat wherever you'd like.
- We get to choose?

1998
01:17:42,911 --> 01:17:45,580
- We want a family portrait look.
- All right.

1999
01:17:45,647 --> 01:17:47,882
- Is this the family portrait look?
- Yes, let's take one like that.

2000
01:17:47,949 --> 01:17:48,950
- Okay.
- Please sit here.

2001
01:17:49,017 --> 01:17:50,585
- Me?
- Yes.

2002
01:17:51,086 --> 01:17:52,687
That's the father's seat.

2003
01:17:54,589 --> 01:18:01,396
THE FATHER ALWAYS SITS ON THE LEFT
IN ALL FAMILY PORTRAITS

2004
01:18:02,063 --> 01:18:03,064
DANIEL GETS THE FATHER'S SEAT

2005
01:18:03,131 --> 01:18:04,499
- Please sit there.
- Okay.

2006
01:18:05,100 --> 01:18:06,835
- Who's the mother?
- Please sit here.

2007
01:18:06,901 --> 01:18:08,837
- Oh, am I the youngest?
- The baby.

2008
01:18:08,903 --> 01:18:10,805
Gosh, my darling.

2009
01:18:10,872 --> 01:18:13,174
- Dad.
- There's my little girl.

2010
01:18:13,241 --> 01:18:14,943
- So you're the dad. Who's the mom?
- Next...

2011
01:18:15,009 --> 01:18:16,544
Please sit here, Do-yeon.

2012
01:18:16,611 --> 01:18:17,679
- Me?
- Yes.

2013
01:18:18,880 --> 01:18:20,849
DANIEL IS THE FATHER

2014
01:18:20,915 --> 01:18:22,183
Mom.

2015
01:18:22,250 --> 01:18:25,520
DO-YEON IS THE MOTHER

2016
01:18:26,388 --> 01:18:29,090
AND...

2017
01:18:29,157 --> 01:18:30,191
That's the pose you want?

2018
01:18:30,925 --> 01:18:32,827
- Don't forget this when you smile.
- Please sit here.

2019
01:18:32,894 --> 01:18:34,095
- Do I sit there?
- Sure.

2020
01:18:34,162 --> 01:18:36,164
The two of you can stand in the back.

2021
01:18:36,231 --> 01:18:37,232
There we go.

2022
01:18:37,298 --> 01:18:38,733
- So Keun-suk stands behind me.
- Yes.

2023
01:18:38,800 --> 01:18:39,901
Let's go for a classical photo.

2024
01:18:39,968 --> 01:18:41,503
- No messing around.
- Let's stiffen up a bit.

2025
01:18:41,569 --> 01:18:42,937
- Stiffen up?
- Okay.

2026
01:18:43,004 --> 01:18:45,573
- Let's all sit up straight.
- A stiff pose first.

2027
01:18:45,640 --> 01:18:48,410
- No smiles?
- Put your hands together.

2028
01:18:52,614 --> 01:18:55,150
- Let me take a few shots first.
- Okay.

2029
01:18:55,216 --> 01:18:56,651
So, one, two.

2030
01:18:57,118 --> 01:19:00,188
HOW IS THEIR FIRST FAMILY PHOTO?

2031
01:19:00,255 --> 01:19:02,457
THE PHOTOS SHOW UP
ON THE SCREEN RIGHT AWAY

2032
01:19:02,524 --> 01:19:03,591
I can't wait.

2033
01:19:09,130 --> 01:19:10,131
EVERYONE LOOKS LIKE A ROBOT

2034
01:19:10,198 --> 01:19:11,466
<i>Oh, no.</i>

2035
01:19:11,533 --> 01:19:12,967
<i>This is hilarious.</i>

2036
01:19:13,435 --> 01:19:14,436
Guys.

2037
01:19:15,003 --> 01:19:16,204
Come on, Do-yeon.

2038
01:19:16,271 --> 01:19:17,639
You're smiling too broadly.

2039
01:19:17,705 --> 01:19:19,474
This is hilarious.

2040
01:19:19,541 --> 01:19:21,009
EYES WIDE OPEN

2041
01:19:21,075 --> 01:19:24,012
HE LOOKS A BIT LIKE CHUCKY

2042
01:19:24,846 --> 01:19:27,415
THE THOUGHT OF HAVING THAT FACE
IN THE LIVING ROOM IS CHILLING

2043
01:19:27,482 --> 01:19:28,750
This is hilarious.

2044
01:19:29,250 --> 01:19:30,285
My abs hurt.

2045
01:19:30,351 --> 01:19:32,754
SQUEALING

2046
01:19:32,821 --> 01:19:33,822
EVERYONE'S AWKWARD

2047
01:19:33,888 --> 01:19:35,857
- What do we do?
- Gosh, what should I do?

2048
01:19:35,924 --> 01:19:37,559
Here's what we'll do.

2049
01:19:38,293 --> 01:19:41,663
Give me your best smiles,
and I'll take a few shots.

2050
01:19:41,729 --> 01:19:43,498
- Okay.
- Let's do as he says.

2051
01:19:43,565 --> 01:19:45,567
Eyes on the camera, please. One, two.

2052
01:19:45,834 --> 01:19:47,836
Give me a smile. One, two.

2053
01:19:49,337 --> 01:19:50,705
One, two.

2054
01:19:50,772 --> 01:19:52,874
A bit more. One, two.

2055
01:19:52,941 --> 01:19:54,943
EYES WIDE OPEN

2056
01:19:56,277 --> 01:19:58,346
LOSING THEIR COOL
AS HE TAKES COUNTLESS SHOTS

2057
01:19:58,413 --> 01:19:59,414
Please look at the camera.

2058
01:19:59,481 --> 01:20:01,182
Give me your best smile. One, two.

2059
01:20:01,249 --> 01:20:03,751
Good. One, two.

2060
01:20:04,285 --> 01:20:09,123
BUT ONE PERSON DID NOT MOVE
EVEN A LITTLE BIT

2061
01:20:09,824 --> 01:20:11,159
Wow, you look great.

2062
01:20:11,226 --> 01:20:13,628
Best smiles, please. One, two.

2063
01:20:14,529 --> 01:20:16,264
What's with that look, Keun-suk?

2064
01:20:16,331 --> 01:20:18,333
- I'm like a robot, right?
- Hey, Keun-suk.

2065
01:20:18,399 --> 01:20:20,068
Keun-suk's like a robot.

2066
01:20:20,768 --> 01:20:22,170
Gosh, Keun-suk.

2067
01:20:22,570 --> 01:20:25,006
PROUD PRINCE'S DEFAULT POSE

2068
01:20:25,073 --> 01:20:30,712
It looks like we're some tourists
taking photos with Keun-suk's cutout.

2069
01:20:30,778 --> 01:20:32,247
The way your skin glows...

2070
01:20:32,313 --> 01:20:34,082
- Like in a fan event?
- Exactly.

2071
01:20:34,148 --> 01:20:35,250
We're in Jang Keun-suk Land.

2072
01:20:35,316 --> 01:20:37,018
"There's Keun-suk's cutout!"

2073
01:20:37,085 --> 01:20:38,119
A CUTOUT FOR YOUR FAMILY PHOTO

2074
01:20:39,454 --> 01:20:41,756
- All right, let's continue.
- Okay.

2075
01:20:41,823 --> 01:20:44,659
You'll be making funny faces next.

2076
01:20:44,993 --> 01:20:47,028
- Funny faces?
- Funny faces?

2077
01:20:47,095 --> 01:20:48,229
Like what, sir?

2078
01:20:49,364 --> 01:20:51,032
UNDERSTANDING RIGHT AWAY

2079
01:20:51,099 --> 01:20:52,901
THAT'S RIGHT UP MY ALLEY

2080
01:20:52,967 --> 01:20:54,035
- Like this?
- Okay.

2081
01:20:54,102 --> 01:20:55,637
One, two. Go.

2082
01:20:55,703 --> 01:20:57,105
IT'S PERFECT FOR THIS FUNNY FAM

2083
01:20:57,171 --> 01:20:59,340
Okay, have a look.

2084
01:20:59,407 --> 01:21:00,408
LAUGHING

2085
01:21:00,475 --> 01:21:02,410
- It's all over the place.
- Hey.

2086
01:21:02,477 --> 01:21:04,112
Only Daniel made a funny face.

2087
01:21:04,178 --> 01:21:06,047
I'm the only one who did it.

2088
01:21:06,114 --> 01:21:07,515
He's the only one who did it.

2089
01:21:07,582 --> 01:21:09,918
How could you, guys?

2090
01:21:09,984 --> 01:21:11,085
LAUGHING HER HEAD OFF

2091
01:21:11,152 --> 01:21:13,521
I'll look as goofy as I can.

2092
01:21:13,588 --> 01:21:15,156
Let's decide first.
Are we doing funny faces?

2093
01:21:15,223 --> 01:21:17,425
Tell me what kind of funny face
I should be making.

2094
01:21:17,492 --> 01:21:18,793
- Show me.
- Just be silly.

2095
01:21:18,860 --> 01:21:20,628
- Let yourself go.
- Just be silly.

2096
01:21:20,695 --> 01:21:22,497
- How far do we let ourselves go?
- Let's see.

2097
01:21:22,797 --> 01:21:23,898
Act as goofy as you can.

2098
01:21:23,965 --> 01:21:25,533
- Goofy?
- Yeah.

2099
01:21:25,600 --> 01:21:27,435
Something silly just like that.

2100
01:21:27,502 --> 01:21:29,137
- Goofy it is.
- Goofy?

2101
01:21:29,404 --> 01:21:30,438
- We're going goofy.
- Yeah.

2102
01:21:30,505 --> 01:21:32,507
- All right. Let's try goofy.
- Let's give it a go.

2103
01:21:32,574 --> 01:21:33,908
Okay. One, two.

2104
01:21:33,975 --> 01:21:35,410
THEY TRY MAKING FUNNY FACES AGAIN!

2105
01:21:35,476 --> 01:21:37,345
A CUTE-GOOFY FACE

2106
01:21:37,412 --> 01:21:39,213
A CHILL-GOOFY FACE

2107
01:21:39,280 --> 01:21:41,516
A GOOFY COMEDIAN

2108
01:21:41,583 --> 01:21:43,484
A BUBBLY-GOOFY FACE

2109
01:21:43,551 --> 01:21:44,886
THE ORIGINAL GOOFY FACE

2110
01:21:44,953 --> 01:21:47,155
GOOFY PRINCE

2111
01:21:48,423 --> 01:21:50,325
<i>- So hilarious.</i>
<i>- What's going on over there?</i>

2112
01:21:51,426 --> 01:21:53,962
<i>What were you doing with your lips?</i>

2113
01:21:54,495 --> 01:21:56,230
What were you doing with your lips?

2114
01:21:56,297 --> 01:21:57,332
AN OLD-SCHOOL TRICK

2115
01:21:57,398 --> 01:21:59,167
That's a nice talent.

2116
01:21:59,934 --> 01:22:01,135
What's with Daniel's lips?

2117
01:22:01,202 --> 01:22:03,404
A bow tie? It's been a while.

2118
01:22:03,471 --> 01:22:05,106
BOW TIES

2119
01:22:05,173 --> 01:22:07,208
- Around our necks...
- Why are we wearing it, though?

2120
01:22:07,275 --> 01:22:08,676
THIS IS A FAMILY PORTRAIT, RIGHT?

2121
01:22:08,743 --> 01:22:10,445
- Here are the props.
- Why are we wearing these?

2122
01:22:10,511 --> 01:22:12,313
- There are black ones.
- It adds more joy.

2123
01:22:12,380 --> 01:22:14,115
To add more joy?
We've got to wear these, then.

2124
01:22:14,983 --> 01:22:16,584
But a bow tie
on a short-sleeve T-shirt...

2125
01:22:16,651 --> 01:22:18,219
- I'm wearing it, but...
- I'm having a blast.

2126
01:22:18,286 --> 01:22:19,487
Is this a proper bow tie, though?

2127
01:22:20,622 --> 01:22:21,623
Thank you all

2128
01:22:21,689 --> 01:22:23,658
for showing so much enthusiasm
for my House Squad Goal.

2129
01:22:23,725 --> 01:22:25,026
This is the best one yet.

2130
01:22:25,093 --> 01:22:27,462
We should've tried
your House Squad Goal first.

2131
01:22:27,528 --> 01:22:28,930
Let me help you.

2132
01:22:28,997 --> 01:22:31,499
We try all sorts of things.

2133
01:22:31,799 --> 01:22:35,370
- You found the perfect place.
- Yes, good job.

2134
01:22:35,436 --> 01:22:37,772
- Thank you.
- You found the perfect place.

2135
01:22:37,839 --> 01:22:41,509
Thank you so much for joining me.

2136
01:22:42,176 --> 01:22:43,177
Let me take a look.

2137
01:22:43,244 --> 01:22:46,080
A FAMILY PORTRAIT
JAE-HYEON HAD LONGED FOR

2138
01:22:46,347 --> 01:22:48,449
<i>- Goodness.</i>
<i>- Hey, I love how I look.</i>

2139
01:22:48,950 --> 01:22:50,251
<i>- How's this?</i>
<i>- This is it for me.</i>

2140
01:22:50,318 --> 01:22:51,452
<i>I love all of them.</i>

2141
01:22:51,519 --> 01:22:52,654
<i>Great work.</i>

2142
01:22:52,720 --> 01:22:55,056
- Give yourselves a big hand.
- Applause!

2143
01:22:55,123 --> 01:22:56,124
JAE-HYEON GOT HIS WISH

2144
01:22:56,190 --> 01:22:57,725
<i>We're done. All the photos look good.</i>

2145
01:22:57,959 --> 01:23:00,695
The bow ties look much better
than I imagined.

2146
01:23:01,362 --> 01:23:02,997
Thanks to your guidance

2147
01:23:03,064 --> 01:23:04,399
- it went so smoothly.
- He's right.

2148
01:23:04,465 --> 01:23:07,168
Thank you.
With such fine models as you

2149
01:23:07,235 --> 01:23:08,870
all shots are bound to be great.

2150
01:23:10,271 --> 01:23:11,973
I do get that a lot.

2151
01:23:12,040 --> 01:23:13,041
ASIA PRINCE'S CONFIDENCE

2152
01:23:13,107 --> 01:23:14,776
Don't you find this funny?

2153
01:23:15,576 --> 01:23:17,445
I think we share a sense of humor.

2154
01:23:17,645 --> 01:23:20,148
When will the framed photo be ready?

2155
01:23:20,381 --> 01:23:23,985
I'll have it ready by tomorrow
and send it with a courier service.

2156
01:23:24,052 --> 01:23:25,920
So we'll get it delivered?

2157
01:23:25,987 --> 01:23:27,321
Okay.

2158
01:23:27,522 --> 01:23:29,123
- We'll look forward to it.
- Thank you.

2159
01:23:29,190 --> 01:23:30,825
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

2160
01:23:30,892 --> 01:23:32,427
<i>I can't wait!</i>

2161
01:23:32,493 --> 01:23:34,028
<i>I can't wait to see the final photo.</i>

2162
01:23:34,095 --> 01:23:37,031
I'm so excited
about seeing the framed photo.

2163
01:23:37,098 --> 01:23:39,567
- There's a joy in waiting.
- That's true.

2164
01:23:39,634 --> 01:23:41,035
- Aren't these yours, Daniel?
- Yes.

2165
01:23:41,102 --> 01:23:42,270
You can leave them there.

2166
01:23:42,336 --> 01:23:43,337
ORGANIZING EVERYONE'S SHOES

2167
01:23:43,404 --> 01:23:44,405
Oh, sure.

2168
01:23:45,006 --> 01:23:48,643
30 MINUTES
BEFORE MS. GAME CHANGER ARRIVES

2169
01:23:48,710 --> 01:23:51,946
CLUELESS ABOUT THE STORM
THAT IS ABOUT TO HIT GUGI-DONG

2170
01:23:52,013 --> 01:23:53,214
Man, that was...

2171
01:23:53,281 --> 01:23:55,683
THE HOUSEMATES HAVE DECIDED
TO HAVE SOME ME TIME

2172
01:23:55,750 --> 01:23:57,118
That was incredible.

2173
01:23:58,319 --> 01:24:03,691
SOO-JIN IS TAKING A REST ON HER BED

2174
01:24:05,226 --> 01:24:07,929
BACK TO DREAMLAND
ONLY 6 HOURS AFTER WAKING UP

2175
01:24:07,995 --> 01:24:09,597
BORN TO HAVE HOUSEMATES

2176
01:24:09,664 --> 01:24:11,532
SOO-JIN NOW SEEMS TO HAVE
DEEP-SLEEP-ITIS

2177
01:24:11,599 --> 01:24:15,670
DO-YEON'S ROOM

2178
01:24:15,737 --> 01:24:18,372
PICKS UP A BOOK

2179
01:24:18,439 --> 01:24:22,176
CLUELESS ABOUT WHAT'S TO COME,
SHE LOSES HERSELF IN THE BOOK

2180
01:24:24,779 --> 01:24:28,015
SHE HASN'T HAD A QUIET AFTERNOON
ALL BY HERSELF IN A WHILE

2181
01:24:28,082 --> 01:24:32,320
ALTHOUGH THE PEACE
WILL BE SHATTERED SOON ENOUGH

2182
01:24:35,456 --> 01:24:38,126
SMOOTHLY INVADING
DO-YEON'S PERSONAL SPACE

2183
01:24:38,392 --> 01:24:39,393
- Don't mind me.
- Water?

2184
01:24:39,460 --> 01:24:40,828
Get back to your own thing.

2185
01:24:40,895 --> 01:24:43,197
It's time for all of us to rest.

2186
01:24:43,264 --> 01:24:45,233
Why did you come into my room, then?

2187
01:24:45,299 --> 01:24:46,434
It's time to rest.

2188
01:24:46,501 --> 01:24:47,535
So rest up.

2189
01:24:47,602 --> 01:24:48,603
Don't even think about...

2190
01:24:48,669 --> 01:24:49,904
It's still full. You didn't use it.

2191
01:24:49,971 --> 01:24:51,038
Don't mind me.

2192
01:24:51,105 --> 01:24:53,141
Was the humidifier not on?

2193
01:24:53,207 --> 01:24:56,010
You don't seem to care that much.

2194
01:24:56,077 --> 01:24:57,945
No, it really is dry in here.

2195
01:24:58,179 --> 01:25:00,548
- It's just that I'm forgetful.
- I see that.

2196
01:25:00,615 --> 01:25:01,983
- It seems like it.
- The habit hasn't stuck with me.

2197
01:25:02,049 --> 01:25:03,985
About your reading habit.

2198
01:25:04,051 --> 01:25:05,620
Try to concentrate
and finish the whole book.

2199
01:25:05,686 --> 01:25:06,821
I can't seem to focus.

2200
01:25:06,888 --> 01:25:08,656
I'M A LOST CAUSE

2201
01:25:08,723 --> 01:25:10,992
You've come at just the right time
after my focus wore off.

2202
01:25:11,058 --> 01:25:13,227
- Did it wear off?
- Yeah.

2203
01:25:15,229 --> 01:25:17,231
SHE HAS HER ME TIME BACK

2204
01:25:17,298 --> 01:25:19,367
FIDDLING

2205
01:25:20,201 --> 01:25:22,970
BUT SHE HAS LOST
THE WILL TO READ ALREADY

2206
01:25:26,941 --> 01:25:29,744
DA-HEE HAS DECIDED TO COME ON OVER
SINCE DO-YEON HAS LOST HER FOCUS

2207
01:25:29,811 --> 01:25:31,512
What's wrong? Don't mind me.

2208
01:25:31,579 --> 01:25:32,980
You really don't have to.

2209
01:25:35,016 --> 01:25:36,184
Want me to go back to my room?

2210
01:25:36,250 --> 01:25:37,852
No, I love this.

2211
01:25:37,919 --> 01:25:40,321
I think it'd be nice to stay put
and chat all the time.

2212
01:25:40,388 --> 01:25:41,389
Same.

2213
01:25:41,455 --> 01:25:42,690
I'VE GIVEN UP ALREADY

2214
01:25:42,757 --> 01:25:44,892
UPSIDE OF LIVING TOGETHER
YOU'RE NOT ALONE

2215
01:25:44,959 --> 01:25:47,795
DOWNSIDE OF LIVING TOGETHER
YOU'RE NOT ALONE

2216
01:25:49,230 --> 01:25:52,867
MEANWHILE,
JAE-HYEON HAS COME DOWNSTAIRS

2217
01:25:54,268 --> 01:25:56,938
MOVING ITEMS ONE BY ONE

2218
01:25:57,805 --> 01:26:01,576
HE'S SUDDENLY CLEANING UP
THE LIVING ROOM

2219
01:26:02,109 --> 01:26:05,913
HE GOES OVER THE ITEMS IN THE FRIDGE

2220
01:26:05,980 --> 01:26:07,849
I should have some fruit
ready for her.

2221
01:26:07,915 --> 01:26:09,951
WHY THE SUDDEN SHOW OF DEFERENCE?

2222
01:26:10,551 --> 01:26:14,655
IT SEEMS HE ISN'T PREPARING THE FRUIT
FOR ONE OF HIS HOUSEMATES

2223
01:26:15,289 --> 01:26:19,861
WHO IS HE GOING
THROUGH THIS TROUBLE FOR?

2224
01:26:21,495 --> 01:26:24,732
AN UNFAMILIAR VEHICLE
APPROACHES THE GUGI-DONG HOUSE

2225
01:26:26,767 --> 01:26:29,370
SOMEONE GETS OUT OF THE CAR

2226
01:26:29,437 --> 01:26:32,974
AN UNFAMILIAR FIGURE WITH LONG HAIR

2227
01:26:33,040 --> 01:26:35,476
WITH A HUGE BAG IN EACH HAND

2228
01:26:35,543 --> 01:26:38,479
SHE RINGS THE BELL
OF THE GUGI-DONG HOUSE

2229
01:26:42,550 --> 01:26:43,551
She's here.

2230
01:26:44,919 --> 01:26:46,254
<i>I got nervous.</i>

2231
01:26:46,320 --> 01:26:47,989
<i>My heart skipped a beat.</i>

2232
01:26:48,923 --> 01:26:50,057
<i>She wasn't one of our housemates.</i>

2233
01:26:50,124 --> 01:26:52,894
<i>It was curious how that alone</i>
<i>made my heart flutter and sing.</i>

2234
01:26:53,361 --> 01:26:54,362
Hello.

2235
01:26:55,763 --> 01:26:56,797
Hi.

2236
01:26:56,864 --> 01:26:59,934
WHO IS MS. GAME CHANGER
WHO'S COME TO ROCK GUGI-DONG HOUSE?

2237
01:27:00,001 --> 01:27:02,436
SPARKED BY A SINGLE SIMPLE REMARK

2238
01:27:02,503 --> 01:27:05,206
A SPONTANEOUS DAY TRIP TO JAPAN

2239
01:27:05,273 --> 01:27:07,308
TWO WAYS TO EXPLORE TOKYO

2240
01:27:07,375 --> 01:27:09,277
The one where you travel alone.

2241
01:27:09,343 --> 01:27:11,045
And the one where you travel with me.

2242
01:27:11,112 --> 01:27:15,082
HOW WOULD THINGS GO IN JAPAN WITH AP?

2243
01:27:15,149 --> 01:27:16,517
PREPARE TO BE AMAZED NON-STOP

2244
01:27:16,584 --> 01:27:18,319
AT THE ULTIMATE LUXURY EXPERIENCE

2245
01:27:18,386 --> 01:27:20,922
HOUSEMATES' TRUE IDENTITIES REVEALED

2246
01:27:21,422 --> 01:27:24,225
FAINTING AT THE INSANE SCALE

2247
01:27:24,725 --> 01:27:26,961
AM I IN HEAVEN?

2248
01:27:27,228 --> 01:27:28,296
NOT QUITE

2249
01:27:28,362 --> 01:27:30,398
A TIME ATTACK FROM HELL

2250
01:27:30,464 --> 01:27:32,199
WITH NO TIME TO ENJOY ANYTHING

2251
01:27:32,266 --> 01:27:34,602
A DAY TRIP IN YOUR FORTIES

2252
01:27:34,669 --> 01:27:36,971
IS IT ROMANTIC

2253
01:27:37,038 --> 01:27:38,306
OR TOTAL MADNESS?

2254
01:27:38,372 --> 01:27:40,608
STORY OF A FAMILY TRIP
THAT ALMOST WENT WRONG

2255
01:27:40,675 --> 01:27:42,376
AN UNPREDICTABLE DAY TRIP WITH AP
WILL IT END WELL?

2256
01:27:42,443 --> 01:27:44,412
<i>I never want to go again.</i>

2257
01:27:46,981 --> 01:27:48,983
Subtitles by Jeongwoo Kim
